{{expert needed|date=April 2011}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Boom Bang-a-Bang: 50 Years of Eurovision | image = | caption = | genre = [[Music]] [[documentary]] | creator = | writer = Colin Edmonds | director = Richard Valentine | presenter = [[Terry Wogan]] | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | num_series = 1 | num_episodes = 1 | list_episodes = | executive_producer = Kevin Bishop | producer = Sarah Gibbs | editor = Kim Nikolajsen | location = [[BBC Television Centre]] | cinematography = | camera = | runtime = 60 minutes | company = BBC Productions | distributor = | channel = [[BBC One]] | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_run = | first_aired = {{Start date|2006|5|16|df=yes}} | status = | related = ''[[Eurovision Song Contest]]'' | website = | website_title = }}
'''''Boom-a-Bang: 50 Years of Eurovision''''' is a one-hour [[documentary]] that aired on [[BBC One]] on 16 May 2006. The programme celebrates 50 years of the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. The programme was presented and narrated by long-serving Eurovision commentator, [[Terry Wogan]].
It included a guest appearance from the [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest|UK]] representative for the [[2006 Eurovision Song Contest]] [[Daz Sampson]], as well as archive footage from previous UK and other entries from previous song contests.<ref>http://www.tvguide.co.uk/titlesearch.asp?title=Boom%20Bang%20a%20Bang:%2050%20Years%20of%20Eurovision</ref>
