Borderline [[Theatre company]] is a touring theatre company based in [[Ayr]], [[Scotland]].
Its alumni include the actors [[Billy Connolly]] and [[Robbie Coltrane]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/4911640.stm |title=Debate call for theatre company |accessdate=2008-02-10 |work=BBC | date=2006-04-15}}</ref> Recent successes include the award-winning, critically acclaimed plays The Wall<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2008/mar/06/theatre3 | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=The Wall | first=Mark | last=Fisher | date=2008-03-06}}</ref><ref>[http://living.scotsman.com/performing-arts/Trips-down-memory-lane.3854191.jp]</ref> and The Ducky<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2009/may/12/review-the-ducky | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=The Ducky | first=Mark | last=Fisher | date=2009-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/theatreblog/2009/may/10/play-sequels-prequels-theatre | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=Stage sequels deserve a second chance | first=Lyn | last=Gardner | date=2009-05-11}}</ref><ref>[http://living.scotsman.com/performing-arts/Theatre-review-The-DuckyBlissMud.5242089.jp]</ref> by [[D C Jackson]].
