[[File:Map of the war in Donbass.svg|thumb|right]]

This is a '''timeline of the [[War in Donbass]]''', from 1 June 2018. The timeline follows an ongoing conflict between Ukraine and anti-government pro-Russian separatists supported by [[Russia]]n [[Russian Armed Forces|troops]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://conflictreport.info/2015/01/23/hard-evidence-the-regular-russian-army-invades-ukraine/|title=Hard evidence, the regular Russian army invades Ukraine|work=Conflict Report|accessdate=1 April 2018 |date=23 April 2015}}</ref> in the [[Donets Basin|Donbass region]] in eastern [[Ukraine]].

{{TOC limit|2}}

== Timeline ==

=== 1 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 26 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--3 WIA--><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/01/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-7-ranku-1-chervnya-2018-rik/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 7 ранку 1 червня 2018 рік |trans-title=|date=1 June 2018 |accessdate=1 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10137734-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-3-wias-amid-26-enemy-attacks.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 3 WIAs amid 26 enemy attacks {{!}} The situation in the zone of the Joint Forces Operation remains under control of Ukrainian troops.|date=2018-06-01 |accessdate=2018-06-01|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> (including on 19 occasions in Donetsk region and on 7 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=_2018-06-01ru>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/01/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-01-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 01 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO: Summary information of 1 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |date=1 June 2018 |accessdate=1 June 2018 |language=ru |quote=Posted By: Galat 13:22 01/06/2018}}</ref>); the fire was returned on about 10 occasions.<ref name=_2018-06-01ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on the last day of May.<ref name=_2018-06-01ru/> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 15 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in nine different locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-15-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 15 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire 15 times– JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-01|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same authorities recorded 66 Ukrainian violations of the truce over the past week. The Ukrainian army fired five rounds from 122 self-propelled artillery, 313 from armoured fighting vehicles and 139 from 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars on the same period.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/01/kievskie-siloviki-pochti-semdesyat-raz-narushili-rezhim-tishiny-basurin/|title=Киевские силовики почти семьдесят раз нарушили режим тишины – Басурин|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-04|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire five times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to engage pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Veselehorivka, Pankivka and Lozove.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mil-lnr.info/press-sluzhba/svodka/item/2733-operativnaya-svodka-za-sutki-s-31-maya-na-1-iyunya|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 31 мая на 1 июня|last=|first=|date=1 June 2018|website=mil.lnr.info|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=1 June 2018}}</ref>

By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 33, as a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded. In the environs of Donetsk city, Ukrainian forces at Marinka, Berezove, Butivka mining complex and Krasnohorivka were attacked with small arms fire and antitank rockets. Ukrainian troops at Slavne were harassed with sniper fire. In the region of Mariupol, [[Chermalyk]] was hit by 122&#160; artillery barrages, while 82&#160; mortar volleys landed in Pavlopil. Rebel forces fired infantry weapons and grenade launchers at Ukrainian positions near Pishchevik, Marinka, Vodiane, Krasnohorivka, Hnutove, Pavlopil, Talakivka and Shyrokyne. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Krymske. Novotoshkivke was shelled with 82&#160; mortars. Troitske, Luhanske, Krymske and Zolote became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-02>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/02/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-2-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 2 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=2 June 2018 |accessdate=2 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> The [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|OSCE]] Special Monitoring Mission to Ukraine reported that 10 civilians were killed and 25 injured in the Donbass region in May.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10138766-osce-smm-confirms-10-killed-and-25-injured-civilians-in-donbas-in-may-alone.html|title=OSCE SMM confirms 10 killed and 25 injured civilians in Donbas in May alone|date=2016-06-01 |accessdate=2018-06-02 |publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials reported a number of Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire throughout the day. In the main incidents, Ukrainian shelling prevented for the third consecutive day the work at Donetsk's water purification plant near Yasynuvata, while troops at [[Kruta Balka, Yasynuvata Raion|Kruta Balka]] were harassed by small arms and heavy machine gun fire. BMP-2 armoured fighting vehicles from Starohnativka riddled pro-Russian redoubts at Bela Kamianka with 30&#160; gunfire.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-krutaya-balka-stskk-4/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Крутой Балке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-v-ocherednoj-raz-sorvali-peresmenku-sotrudnikov-dfs-stskk/ ВСУ в очередной раз сорвали пересменку сотрудников ДФС — СЦКК / AFU once again thwarted the shift turnover of DFS staff – JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-belaya-kamenka-stskk Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Белой Каменке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].</ref>

=== 2 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 33 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-02/><!--1 WIA--> (including on 26 occasions in Donetsk region and on 7 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-02/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-02/> By 11:00&nbsp;am of 2 June nine ceasefire violations were registered, two Ukrainian soldiers were wounded.<ref name=OOS-06-02/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in the Donbass region on the first day of June.<ref name=OOS-06-02>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/02/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-02-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 02 июня 2018 |trans-title=|date=2 June 2018 |accessdate=2 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 14:10 02/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials in Donetsk city recorded three Ukrainian violations of the truce. The Ukrainian military used small arms, heavy machine guns, 82&#160; mortars and BMP-2 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Kruta Balka, Zaitseve and Bela Kamianka.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-primenili-56-boepripasov-po-territorii-dnr-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ применили 56 боеприпасов по территории ДНР — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-02|language=ru-RU}}</ref> No violations of the truce were reported by the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mil-lnr.info/press-sluzhba/svodka/item/2738-operativnaya-svodka-za-sutki-s-1-iyunya-na-2-iyunya|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 1 июня на 2 июня|last=|first=|date=2 June 2018|website=mil-lnr.info|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2 June 2018}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on multiple occasions, three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Opytne became the target of antitank rockets and antitank guided missiles. Ukrainian troops at Marinka, Taramchuk and Krasnohorivka were fired at from rocket launchers. Sniper activity was reported at Marinka and Avdiivka. In the region of Mariupol, Lebedinske, Vodiane and Chermalik came under 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar fire, while rocket propelled grenades landed in Chermalyk, Vodiane, Hnutove, Lebedinske, Pavlopil and Shyrokyne. Ukrainian troops at Pavlopil were harassed by hostile snipers. In the northern section of the demarcation line, heavy shelling was reported around Krymske and Luhanske, which were shelled with rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Ukrainian positions in the area were also engaged by pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles. Yuzhne, Zaitseve and Novotoskivke were struck by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and 82&#160;mm mortar volleys.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/380548399104449?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 2 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-02 |accessdate=2018-06-02 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 28 ceasefire violations were registered.<ref name=FB7am_06-03>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/380784945747461?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 7:00 03 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-03 |accessdate=2018-06-03 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10139621-ukraine-s-army-eliminates-three-enemy-fighters-in-donbas-in-past-day.html |title=Ukraine's army eliminates three enemy fighters in Donbas in past day {{!}} The situation in the Joint Forces Operation zone remains tense, but is under control.|date=2018-06-03 |accessdate=2018-06-03|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces had broken the ceasefire on several occasions by evening. Yasynuvata, Dokuchaievsk, Yakovliivka and Vasiilivka, in the environs of Donetsk city, Gagarin mining complex, Zaitseve, Shyroka Balka and Holmivsky, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Bela Kamianka, Nikolaevka and Uzhivka came under attack. In the main incidents, 120&#160;mm mortar rounds landed in Yasynuvata, Dokuchaievsk, Yakovliivka, Zaitseve, Holmivsky and Nikolaevka. Zaitseve and Uzhivka were also hit by 82&#160;mm mortar fire. BMP-2 armoured fighting vehicles from Novotroitske and Starohnativka riddled pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk and Bela Kamianka with 30&#160; gunfire. Zaitseve, Gagarin mining complex and [[Shyroka Balka]] were targeted by 73&#160; antitank recoilless rifles.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-yasinovatoj-i-zajtsevo-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Ясиноватой и Зайцево - СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-yakovlevke-gorlovke-i-beloj-kamenke-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Яковлевке, Горловке и Белой Каменке - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-yasinovatuyu-iz-minometa-stskk/ ВСУ ведут обстрел Ясиноватой из миномета - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-ryadu-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk-2/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по ряду населенных пунктов Республики - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-v-ocherednoj-raz-obstrelyali-naselennye-punkty-na-gorlovskom-i-mariupolskom-napravleniyah-stskk/ ВСУ в очередной раз обстреляли населенные пункты на Горловском и Мариупольском направлениях - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-zajtsevo-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Зайцево - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 3 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 28 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--3 WIA--><ref name=FB7am_06-03/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10139621-ukraine-s-army-eliminates-three-enemy-fighters-in-donbas-in-past-day.html |title=Ukraine's army eliminates three enemy fighters in Donbas in past day {{!}} The situation in the Joint Forces Operation zone remains tense, but is under control.|date=2018-06-03 |accessdate=2018-06-04|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> (including on 23 occasions in Donetsk region and on 5 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-03/>); the fire was returned on 12 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-03/> By morning of 3 June four ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned twice.<ref name=OOS-06-03/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 2 June.<ref name=OOS-06-03>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/03/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-03-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 03 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 3 June 2018 |date=3 June 2018 |accessdate=3 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 12:26 03/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 20 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in ten different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-dvadtsat-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ двадцать раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sources from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded four Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Kalynynove, Sokolniki, Donetskyi and Zholobok using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mil-lnr.info/press-sluzhba/svodka/item/2745-operativnaya-svodka-za-sutki-so-2-iyunya-na-3-iyunya|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки со 2 июня на 3 июня|last=|first=|date=3 June 2018|website=mil-lnr.info|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref>

By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 27, with no casualties on the Ukrainian side. In the area around Donetsk city, Novotroitske and Avdiivka came under 120&#160;mm and 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire respectively. Infantry weapons and grenade launchers were fired at Marinka, Krasnohorivka, Taramchuk, Avdiivka and Novotroitske. In the region of Mariupol, 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery and 82&#160; mortars shelled Hnutove. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Vodiane, while 120&#160;mm mortar volleys struck Lebedinske. Ukrainian troops at Shyrokyne, Vodiane, Novotroitske, Avdiivka, Hnutovo, Nikolaevka, Pavlopil and Lebedinske became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, rebel forces opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Zolote, Zaitseve, Krymske, Yuzhne and Novoluhanske. Later, Zaitseve was hit by 82&#160;mm mortar rounds.<ref name=MoD7am06-04>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/04/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-4-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 4 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=4 June 2018 |accessdate=4 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities recorded multiple ceasefire violations by Ukrainian forces throughout the day. The Ukrainian military attacked Dokuchaievsk, Spartak and Trudivske, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Zaitseve, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Nova Tavriya, Uzhivka, Pikuzy, Dzerzhinske, Sakhanka and Bezimenne. In the main incidents, Dokuchaievsk was repeatedly shelled with 73&#160;mm antitank rifles and 120&#160;mm mortars; power lines, gas pipelines and a number of houses were heavily damaged. Pro-Russian redoubts at Pikuzy were engaged by 122&#160;mm self-propelled guns firing from Talakivka. Pikuzy was also targeted by 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars; 120&#160;mm mortar rounds also landed in Nova Tavriya. Zaitseve, Spartak, Sakhanka and Bezimenne came under 82&#160; mortar fire. The same sources also reported that Ukrainian troops planted antitank mines along the approaches of Donetsk's water purification plant.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-v-dokuchaevske-povrezhdeny-zhilye-doma-lep-i-gazoprovod/ В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ в Докучаевске повреждены жилые дома, ЛЭП и газопровод].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-vsu-po-leninskomu-stskk-2/ Зафиксирован обстрел ВСУ по Ленинскому - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-spartak-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Спартак - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/ukrainskaya-storona-miniruet-dorogi-vedushhie-k-donetskoj-filtrovalnoj-stantsii-foto/ Украинская сторона минирует дороги, ведущие к Донецкой фильтровальной станции (фото)].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-aleksandrovke-obstrelom-vsu-razbit-dom-stskk/ В Александровке обстрелом ВСУ разбит дом - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-obstrel-territorii-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ ведут обстрел территории Республики - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-stskk-5/ ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 4 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 27 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref name=MoD7am06-04/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10140098-jfo-russian-led-forces-mount-27-attacks-on-ukraine-army-in-donbas-in-past-day.html |title=JFO: Russian-led forces mount 27 attacks on Ukraine army in Donbas in past day {{!}} One enemy troop was killed, intelligence reports said.|date=2018-06-04 |accessdate=2018-06-04|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> (including on 21 occasions in Donetsk region and on 6 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-04/>); the fire was returned on 13 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-04/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 3 June.<ref name=OOS-06-04>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/04/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-04-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 04 июня 2018 |trans-title=|date=4 June 2018 |accessdate=4 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:21 04/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 16 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in ten different locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. One pro-Russian soldier was killed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-16-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-povrezhdeny-zhilye-doma-stskk/|title=ВСУ 16 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня, повреждены жилые дома — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire 16 times, residential buildings are damaged – JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-04|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/obstrelami-vsu-povrezhdeny-doma-pogib-odin-voennosluzhashhij-dnr-eduard-basurin/|title=Обстрелами ВСУ повреждены дома, погиб один военнослужащий ДНР – Эдуард Басурин (видео) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-04|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire seven times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Lozove, Kalynove, Prishib and Kalynivka employing heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars and 120&#160;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/04/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-chetyre-poselka-5/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка — обстреляны четыре поселка|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-04|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/381479475678008?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 4 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-04 |accessdate=2018-06-04 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 30 ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side. In the surroundings of Donetsk city, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles launched an attack on Ukrainian positions at Avdiivka. Ukrainian forces near Avdiivka and Pisky were fired at from ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns some hours later. Novotroitske was shelled with 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. Ukrainian troops at Nevelske, Marinka and Krasnohorivka were attacked with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, rebel forces used infantry weapons and grenade launchers to harass Ukrainian troops at Pavlopil, Lebedinske and Vodiane. In the northern section of the demarcation line, 122&#160;mm self-propelled gund fired on Ukrainian redoubts at Novotoshkivke; the same positions were hit by 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar rounds. Zaitseve and Krymske received 82&#160;mm mortar fire. In addition, Ukrainian positions at Lozove, Krymske and Luhanske were hit by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and antitank rockets. Hours later, Krymske came under attack from armoured fighting vehicles supported by small arms, rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160; mortars.<ref name=MoD7am06-05/> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on several occasions throughout the day. The Ukrainian army attacked pro-Russian positions around Yasynuvata, Trudivske, Dokuchaievsk, Spartak and Zhabicheve, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Zaitseve, Ozeryanivka, Dolomitne and Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka and Novomakiivka, in the region of Mariupol. In the main incidents, Zaitseve was repeatedly targeted by small arms, automatic grenade launchers, antitank rockets and 120&#160;mm mortars. Spartak and Zhabicheve were hit by 82&#160;mm mortar rounds, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Hranitne and Novotroitske engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Novomakiivka and Dokuchaievsk.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-razrushili-chastnyj-dom-v-zajtsevo/ ВСУ разрушили частный дом в Зайцево].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-i-yasinovatuyu-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево и Ясиноватую - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-ogon-po-territorii-respubliki-stskk-5/ ВСУ ведут огонь по территории Республики - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-gorlovku-i-zajtsevo-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Горловку и Зайцево - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-dokuchaevsk-i-ozeryanovku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево, Докучаевск и Озеряновку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-zajtsevo-dolomitnomu-i-dokuchaevsku-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Зайцево, Доломитному и Докучаевску - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-zajtsevo-zhabichevo-i-spartaku-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Зайцево, Жабичево и Спартаку - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 5 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 30 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref name=MoD7am06-05>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/05/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-7-ranku-5-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 7 ранку 5 червня 2018 рік |trans-title=|date=5 June 2018 |accessdate=5 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10141478-jfo-ukraine-reports-30-enemy-attacks-in-last-day.html |title=JFO: Ukraine reports 30 enemy attacks in last day {{!}} Two enemy troops were killed and another six were wounded, Ukraine's intelligence said.|date=2018-06-05 |accessdate=2018-06-05|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> (including on 19 occasions in Donetsk region and on 11 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-05/>); the fire was returned on 17 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-05/> By 11:00&nbsp;am of 5 June eleven ceasefire violations were registered<ref name=OOS-06-05/> and one [[Orlan-10]] drone was shot down.<ref name=FB_6pm_06-05/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 4 June.<ref name=OOS-06-05>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/05/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-05-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 05 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 5 June 2018 |date=5 June 2018 |accessdate=5 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 12:41 05/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported 16 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in ten different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, snipers, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-16-raz-povrezhdeny-doma-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ нарушили режим прекращения огня 16 раз, повреждены дома — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire 16 times during the day, houses are damaged – JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on four occasions within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenades launchers, antitank rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to pound pro-Russian redoubts at Zholobok, Donetskyi, and Kalynivka.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/05/operativnaya-svodka-po-lnr-obstrelyany-pgt-donetskij-syola-zhelobok-i-kalinovka-zhertv-net/|title=Оперативная сводка по ЛНР: обстреляны пгт Донецкий, сёла Желобок и Калиновка, жертв нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 17 occasions, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded;<ref name=FB_6pm_06-05>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/381912982301324 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 5 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-05 |accessdate=2018-06-05 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> by the end of the day total 31 ceasefire violations were registered, one more Ukrainain soldier was wounded. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian positions supported by 82&#160; mortar fire; 82&#160; mortar volleys also landed in Novotroitske. Infantry weapons and rocket launchers were used to harass Ukrainiian troops at Krasnohorivka, Avdiivka, Pisky, Berezove, Verkhnyotoretske and Marinka. In the region of Mariupol, Ukrainian forces at Talakivka, Pavlopil, Vodiane, Shyrokyne, Pyshchevik and Hnutove became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian redoubts around Krymske supported by heavy machine guns, grenade launchers, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar fire. Novotoshkivke became the target of 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars, while Luhanske, Stanytsia Luhanska and Orekhove were struck by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and antitank rockets.<ref name=MoD7am06-06>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/06/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-7-ranku-6-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 6 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=6 June 2018 |accessdate=6 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-06" /> Sources from the self-proclaimed Donetsk People's Republic reported multiple ceasefire violations by Ukrainian forces throughout the day. Dokuchaievsk, Spartak and Donetsk airport, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, and in the area of Horlivka, Zaitseve and Shyroka Balka, came under attack. Dokuchaievsk was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars, while Spartak and Donetsk airport came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Novhorodske launched an attack on pro-Russian positions at Shyroka Balka. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novotroitske raked pro-Russian redoubts at Dokuchaievsk with 30&#160;mm gunfire. Donetsk airport was targeted by 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless guns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-stskk-6/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-06|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-ryadu-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk-3/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по ряду населенных пунктов Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-06|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 6 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 31 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-06/><!--3 WIA--> (including on 21 occasions in Donetsk region and on 10 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-06/>); the fire was returned on 16 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-06/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 6 June three ceasefire violations were registered.<ref name=OOS-06-06/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 5 June.<ref name=OOS-06-06>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/06/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-06-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 04 июня 2018 |trans-title=|date=6 June 2018 |accessdate=6 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:08 06/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city said that there were seven Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in five different locations using small arms, antitank rocket launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-7-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-povrezhden-zhiloj-dom-stskk/|title=ВСУ 7 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня, поврежден жилой дом — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-06|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-06|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sources from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded four Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Kalynynivka, Sokolniki and Zholobok using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref name="news-front.info">{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/06/lnr-obstrelyany-tri-poselka-za-sutki/|title=ЛНР: обстреляны три поселка за сутки|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-06|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 7 occasions, no casualties were reported. Ukrainian forces fired back.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/382290938930195?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 6 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-06 |accessdate=2018-06-06 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 25 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, two Ukrainian servicemen were killed and two were wounded. In the environs of Donetsk city, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar volleys hit Opytne. Pro-Russian armed forces harassed Ukrainian troops with small arms and machine gun fire at Marinka, Nevelske and Avdiivka. In the region of Mariupol, Ukrainian positions at Shyrokyne, Pyshchevik, Hnutove, Pavlopil and Vodiane became the target of infantry weapons. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Krymske, Novozvanivka and Luhanske, supported by small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Some hours later, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar volleys landed in Novotoshkivke, while 82&#160;mm mortars were fired at Krymske.<ref name=MoD7am06-07>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/07/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-ranku-7-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 7 ранку 7 червня 2018 рік |trans-title=|date=7 June 2018 |accessdate=7 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces had attacked Yasynuvata with small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers and 82&#160; mortars during the evening. Donetsk's water purification plant was put out of commission. Several power lines were damaged. Zaitseve became the target of small arms and 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless guns.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-yasinovatoj-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Ясиноватой — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obestochili-dfs-minometnym-obstrelom-stskk/ ВСУ обесточили ДФС минометным обстрелом — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryvali-ogon-po-yasinovatoj-stskk/ ВСУ открывали огонь по Ясиноватой — СЦКК]<br /></ref><ref name="Официальный сайт ДНР">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-3-raza-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-povrezhdena-lep-pitayushhaya-dfs-stskk/|title=ВСУ 3 раза нарушили режим прекращения огня, повреждена ЛЭП, питающая ДФС — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-07|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-07|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 7 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 25 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--2 KIA, 2 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-07/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10144130-jfo-ukraine-reports-2-kia-s-2-wia-s-amid-25-enemy-attacks-in-past-day.html |title=JFO: Ukraine reports 2 KIA's, 2 WIA's amid 25 enemy attacks in past day {{!}} Five members of the Russian occupation forces were killed and another three were wounded, according to Ukrainian intelligence reports.|date=2018-06-07 |accessdate=2018-06-07|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> (including on 21 occasions in Donetsk and on 4 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-07/>); the fire was returned on 15 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-07/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 7 June seven ceasefire violations were registered, with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref name=OOS-06-07/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were killed in action and another two were wounded in the Donbass region on 6 June.<ref name=OOS-06-07>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/07/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-07-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 07 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 7 June 2018 |date=7 June 2018 |accessdate=7 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:23 07/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported three Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in two locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 82&#160;mm mortars.<ref name="Официальный сайт ДНР"/> Authorities from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded five Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Pankivka, Kalynove, Lozove, Donetskyi and Molodezhne using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref name="news-front.info"/>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 17 occasions, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action.<ref name=FB_6pm_06-07>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/382666332225989?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 7 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-07 |accessdate=2018-06-07 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 37, another two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Ukrainian forces at Opytne were engaged by snipers and armoured fighting vehicles. The separatists fired heavy machine guns and rocket propelled grenades at Marinka, Nevelske, Avdiivka, Pisky, Novotroitske, Novoselivka and Kamianka. In the region of Mariupol, heavy shelling was reported at Vodiane, which became the target of 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160; self-propelled guns. Lebedinske came under 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar fire. Ukrainian troops at Shyrokyne, Hnutove, Vodiane and Pavlopil were fired at from heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Pro-Russian tanks launched a sustained attack on Ukrainian redoubts Novotoshkivke, in the northern section of the demarcation line, supported by heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured fighting vehicles and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. The nearby strongholds of Zaitseve and Krymske were shelled with 82&#160; mortars. Ukrainian positions at Krymske, Novozvanivka, Luhanske, Lozove and Troitske came under fire from small arms, heavy machine guns and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref name=MoD7am06-08>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/08/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-ranku-8-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 8 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=8 June 2018 |accessdate=8 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources reported a number of Ukrainian violations of the truce by evening. Ukrainian forces opened fire at Zaitseve, in the area of Horlivka, and, in the region of Mariupol, at Sakhanka and Pikuzy. Pro-Russian positions at Zaitseve were targeted by 73&#160; antitank recoilless guns for the second consecutive day. The area was also hit by automatically launched grenades and antitank rockets. Sakhanka was meanwhile attacked with antitank guided missiles, and Pikuzy was struck by 120&#160;mm mortar rounds fired from Shyrokyne. In the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic, mortar rounds landed in a street of Holubovske, hitting a bus and seriously injuring six civilian residents.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-minometnogo-obstrela-vsu-poselka-golubovskoe-lnr-postradali-6-chelovek-stskk/ В результате минометного обстрела ВСУ поселка Голубовское (ЛНР) пострадали 6 человек - СЦКК / Due to the AFU’s mortar shelling on the village of Golubovskoye (LPR), 6 people are injured – JCCC].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-kominternovo/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Коминтерново].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-sahanku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливали Саханку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/so-storony-vsu-zafiksirovan-obstrel-po-zajtsevo-stskk/ Со стороны ВСУ зафиксирован обстрел по Зайцево - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 8 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 37 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--4 WIA--> (including on 23 occasions in Donetsk region and on 14 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-08/>);<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10145540-escalation-in-donbas-ukraine-reports-4-wia-s-amid-37-enemy-attacks.html |title=Escalation in Donbas: Ukraine reports 4 WIA's amid 37 enemy attacks {{!}} According to intelligence reports, one enemy troop was killed and two others were wounded.|date=2018-06-08 |accessdate=2018-06-08|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> the fire was returned on about 20 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-08/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 8 June seven ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, two Ukrainian soldiers were wounded.<ref name=OOS-06-08/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 7 June.<ref name=OOS-06-08>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/08/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-08-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 08 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 8 June 2018|date=8 June 2018 |accessdate=8 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:16 08/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported four Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in four locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and antitank guided missiles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-4-raza-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-sem-naselennyh-punktov-ostavalis-bez-elektrichestva-stskk/|title=ВСУ 4 раза нарушили режим прекращения огня, семь населенных пунктов оставались без электричества — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-08|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same sources said that Ukrainian forces broke the truce 68 times over the past week. The Ukrainian army fired seven shells from 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery, 26 from 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars and 203 rounds from armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/08/vs-dnr-boeviki-vsu-gotovyatsya-zanyat-seruyu-zonu-v-rajone-n-p-petrovskoe/|title=ВС ДНР: Боевики ВСУ готовятся занять "серую зону" в районе н.п. Петровское|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-10|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Officials from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded five Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Holubovske, Donetskyi and Zholobok using small arms, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/08/vsu-pyat-raz-narushili-rezhim-tishiny-narodnaya-militsiya-lnr/|title=ВСУ пять раз нарушили режим тишины – Народная милиция ЛНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-08|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 5:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian military forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 17 occasions<!-- this (2 WIA=, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded) was reported earlier-->.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/383069518852337?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 17:00 8 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-08 |accessdate=2018-06-08 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 38 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, six Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. Around Donetsk city, pro-Russian forces opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Krasnohorivka and Marinka with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Sniper fire was reported at Krasnohorivka. In the region of Mariupol, 120&#160;mm mortar rounds hit Vodiane and Shyrokyne. The separatists used infantry weapons and grenade launchers to attack Ukrainian positions at Pavlopil, Marinka and Hnutove. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian forces at Krymske and Novotoshkivke, supported by small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. Infantry weapons, grenade launchers, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars were also fired at Zalizne, Katerinivka, Luhanske and Zaitseve.<ref name=OOS-06-09/><ref name=MoD7am06-09>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/09/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-7-ranku-9-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 7 ранку 7 червня 2018 рік |trans-title=|date=9 June 2018 |accessdate=9 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Multiple Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire were reported by pro-Russian sources throughout the day. Yasynuvata and Mineralne, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Zaitseve and Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka, and Sakhanka, in the region of Mariupol, came under attack. In the main incidents, Sakhanka was hit by 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar rounds, while 82&#160;mm mortar volleys landed in Mineralne, Zaitseve and Gagarin mining complex. Pro-Russian positions at Yasynuvata were hit by 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles. Two civilian residents were wounded.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-mineralnoe-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Минеральное - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-gorlovke-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Горловке - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-zajtsevo-ranen-mirnyj-zhitel-ivan-prihodko/ В Зайцево ранен мирный житель - Иван Приходько].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-i-sahanku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево и Саханку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-sahanku-i-yasinovatuyu-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Саханку и Ясиноватую - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-hode-obstrela-sahanki-postradal-mirnyj-zhitel-stskk/ В ходе обстрела Саханки пострадал мирный житель - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 9 June === 
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 38 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--6 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-09/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10146746-militants-suffer-losses-trying-to-knock-joint-forces-off-their-positions-in-donbas.html |title=Militants suffer losses trying to knock Joint Forces off their positions in Donbas {{!}} Russian proxy forces violated the ceasefire regime 38 times, including nine times with the use of weapons banned by Minsk agreements.|date=2018-06-09 |accessdate=2018-06-09|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> (including on 24 occasions in Donetsk and on 14 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-09/>); the fire was returned on 17 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-09/> By morning of 9 June six ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned on 4 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-09/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that six Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 8 June.<ref name=OOS-06-09>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/09/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-09-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 09 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 9 June 2018 |date=9 June 2018 |accessdate=9 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 12:39 09/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported eight Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in six locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars and 120&#160;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-8-raz-raneny-mirnye-zhiteli-povrezhdeny-doma-stskk/|title=ВСУ применили по территории Республики 93 боеприпаса, ранены мирные жители, повреждены дома — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-09|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref> In the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic, local officials reported three Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire. The Ukrainian military used small arms, rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to pound pro-Russian positions at Krasnyi Yar and Donetskyi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/09/obstrely-lnr-povrezhdyon-detskij-sad-v-posyolke-donetskom/|title=Обстрелы ЛНР – повреждён детский сад в посёлке Донецком|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/382666332225989?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation |date=2018-06-09 |accessdate=2018-06-09 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 30, another Ukrainian serviceman was wounded. In the area of Donetsk city, Novoselivka was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars, while Opytne and Pisky were hit by 82&#160;mm mortar volleys. Marinka and Novotroitske was hit by heavy machine gun fire and rocket propelled grenades. In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Pyshchevik, while infantry weapons and grenade launchers were used to harass Ukrainian troops at Pavlopil, Hnutove, Vodiane and Lebedinske. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Novotoshkivke was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars. Ukrainian positions at Krymske, Novozvanivka, Luhanske, Svitlodarsk and Zolote were fired at from small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-10>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/10/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-10-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 10 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10147202-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-2-wia-s-amid-30-enemy-attacks.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 2 WIA's amid 30 enemy attacks {{!}} Hostilities continued in several directions, mainly with the use of grenade launchers and small arms.|date=2018-06-10 |accessdate=2018-06-10|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-10" /> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces had broken the ceasefire several times by evening. The Ukrainian military attacked Yakovliivka, Dokuchaievsk, Vasiilivka and Yasynuvata, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, and Zaitseve, in the area of Horlivka. In the main incidents, Zaitseve, Yakovliivka and Yasynuvata became the target of 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 82&#160;mm mortars. Sniper fire was reported at Vasiilivka, where a civilian woman was wounded.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-yakovlevke-stskk/ ВСУ стреляли из минометов и гранатометов по территории Республики - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-dokuchaevsku-i-yakovlevke-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Докучаевску и Яковлевке - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-yasinovatuyu-iz-minometa-i-granatometa-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливали Ясиноватую из миномета и гранатомета - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-vasilevki-ranena-zhenshhina-stskk/ В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ Васильевки ранена женщина - СЦКК и МО ДНР].</ref><ref name=":5" />

=== 10 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 30 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-10/><!--2 WIA--> (including on 22 occasions in Donetsk region and on 8 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-06-10_uk/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-06-10_uk/> By morning of 10 June (as of 9:00&nbsp;am) five ceasefire violations were registered; the fire was returned at least once.<ref name=MoD_1230-06-10_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 9 June.<ref name=MoD_1230-06-10_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/10/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-06-10 |accessdate=2018-06-10 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref name=OOS-06-10>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/10/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-10-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 10 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 10 June 2018|date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:53 10/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported six Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in six locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, snipers, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars.<ref name=":5">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-strelyali-iz-minometov-i-granatometov-po-territorii-respubliki-stskk/|title=ВСУ стреляли из минометов и гранатометов по территории Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-10|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-10|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on two occasions within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Kalynove and Lozove.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://donetsk24.su/news/operativnaia-svodka-za-sutki-s-9-iiunia-na-10-iiunia-ot-nm-lnr/|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 9 июня на 10 июня от НМ ЛНР|last=24|first=Донецк|website=Донецк 24|language=Russian|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 7 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/384080542084568?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 10 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-10 |accessdate=2018-06-10 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 32 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the surroundings of Donetsk city, 82&#160;mm mortar rounds hit Opytne. Ukrainian forces at Avdiivka, Krasnohorivka, Marinka, Verkhnyotoretske and Novotroitske became the target of heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. In the region of Mariupol, Lebedinske and Vodiane were struck by 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar barrages. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles attacked Pavlopil supported by 120&#160;mm mortar fire. The separatists fired heavy machine guns and rocket launchers at Ukrainian positions around Hnutove, Talakivka, Shyrokyne and Pavlopil. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, heavy shlling was reported at Novotoshkivke, which was pounded by 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Ukrainian positions at Luhanske, Orekhove, Mayorsk and Zaitseve were attacked with infantry weapons and rocket launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-11>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/11/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-11-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 11 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=11 June 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10147733-day-in-donbas-militants-fail-to-penetrate-ukraine-s-defenses-suffering-losses.html |title=Day in Donbas: Militants fail to penetrate Ukraine's defenses, suffering losses {{!}} As of the morning of Monday, June 11, three WIAs and 1 KIA are reported among terrorists.|date=2018-06-11 |accessdate=2018-06-11|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-11" /> Pro-Russian officials reported a number of Ukrainian violations of the truce by evening. Trudivske and Dokuchaievsk, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, and, in the area of Horlivka, Verkhnyotoretske and Gagarin mining complex came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Marinka launched an attack on Trudivske supported by 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar fire; several civilian residences were damaged. Gagarin mining complex, meanwhile, became the target of automatic grenade launchers, ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. Dokuchaievsk and Verkhnyotoretske were fired at from 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless guns.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-trudovskie-i-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Трудовские и Докучаевск - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-poluchili-povrezhdeniya-domostroeniya-v-mikrorajone-trudovskie-donetska-stskk/ В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ получили повреждения домостроения в микрорайоне Трудовские Донецка - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-gorlovku-i-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают Горловку и Докучаевск - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-verhnetoretskoe-nizhnee-stskk-3/ ВСУ обстреляли Верхнеторецкое (нижнее) - СЦКК].</ref> Pro-Russian troops recovered and handed back the corpses of two Ukrainian fighters killed in no-man's land on 28 May near Pisky.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/10/v-dnr-evakuirovali-tela-dvuh-ukrainskih-diversantov-pogibshih-v-mae/|title=В ДНР эвакуировали тела двух украинских диверсантов, погибших в мае|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-12|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/ukrainskoj-storone-vernuli-tela-pogibshih-diversantov-mo-dnr/|title=Украинской стороне вернули тела погибших диверсантов — МО ДНР {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-11|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-12|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Work at Donetsk water purification plant resumed work as usual after three days of inactivity. The facilities had been left without power after heavy shelling on 7 May.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/donetskaya-filtrovalnaya-stantsiya-vozobnovila-rabotu-v-shtatnom-rezhime-stskk/|title=Донецкая фильтровальная станция возобновила работу в штатном режиме — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-09|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-12|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 11 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 32 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--3 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-11/> (including on 23 occasions in Donetsk and on 9 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-11/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-11/> By morning of 11 June three ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side (as of 7:00&nbsp;am).<ref name=OOS-06-11/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 10 June.<ref name=OOS-06-11>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/11/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-11-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 11 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 11 June 2018 |date=11 June 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:29 11/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported four Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in four locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-gorlovku-verhnetoretskoe-dokuchaevsk-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреливали Горловку, Верхнеторецкое, Докучаевск — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-11|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-11|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Authorities from the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on one occasion within the republic's borders, when 73&#160; antitank recoilless guns from Prichepilivka were fired at Zholobok.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/11/operativnaya-svodka-po-lnr-obstrel-poselka-zhelobok/|title=Оперативная сводка по ЛНР — обстрел поселка Желобок|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-11|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in action.<ref name=FB_6pm_06-11>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/384524245373531?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 11 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-11 |accessdate=2018-06-11 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 27, another two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the environs of Donetsk city, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars were fired at Ukrainian positions around Kamianka, Novotroitske and Pisky. Separatist troops fired infantry weapons and rocket launchers at Ukrainian forces holding Avdiivka, Kamianka and Marinka. In the region of Mariupol, 122&#160;mm artillery barrages struck Shyrokyne, and 82&#160;mm mortar volleys landed in Vodiane and Lomakine. Hours later, Hnutove, Vodiane and Lomakine came under attack from armoured fighting vehicles. Infantry weapons and grenade lanchers were used to harass Ukrainian troops at Pavlopil and Hnutove. In the northern section of the demarcation line, 122&#160;mm self-propelled guns shelled Novotoshkivke; the Ukrainian stronghold was also hit by 120&#160;mm mortar rounds, as well as Svitlodarsk. Nearby Troitske became the target of 82&#160; mortars. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles, supported by small arms and heavy machine guns, opened fire on Novozvanivka, Svitlodarsk and Popasna.<ref name=MoD7am06-12>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/12/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-12-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 12 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=12 June 2018 |accessdate=12 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10149251-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-3-wia-s-amid-27-enemy-attacks.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 3 WIA's amid 27 enemy attacks {{!}} According to intelligence reports, two occupiers were killed and three others were wounded.|date=2018-06-12 |accessdate=2018-06-12|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-12" /> Pro-Russian officials told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on a number of occasions throughout the day. Spartak, Volvo Center and Dokuchaievsk, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, and Uzhivka, in the region of Mariupol, were the scene of Ukrainian attacks. In the main incidents, Spartak and Volvo Center were hit by 120&#160;mm mortar fire; two civilian workers were seriously injured. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novotroitske raked pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk with 30&#160;mm gunfire.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/utrom-vsu-obstrelyali-leninskoe-stskk/ Утром ВСУ обстреляли Ленинское - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-kujbyshevskij-rajon-donetska-raneno-tri-cheloveka/ ВСУ обстреляли Куйбышевский район Донецка, ранены три человека (фото + видео)].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-spartak-i-volvo-tsentr-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Спартак и "Вольво-центр" - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-dokuchaevsku-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Докучаевску — СЦКК].</ref>

=== 12 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 27 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-12/><!--3 WIA--> (including on 18 occasions in Donetsk region and on 9 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-12/>); the fire was returned on 14 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-12/> By morning of 12 June (as of 9:00&nbsp;am) six ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, two Ukrainian servicemen were injured.<ref name=OOS-06-12/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 11 June.<ref name=OOS-06-12>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/12/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-12-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 12 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 12 June 2018|date=12 June 2018 |accessdate=12 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:59 12/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported six Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in six different locations using small arms, snipers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles. one pro-Russian soldier was killed in action.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-obstrelyali-ryad-naselennyh-punktov-est-ranenye-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ обстреляли ряд населенных пунктов, есть раненые — СЦКК / AFU shelled several populated localities during the day, there are victims – JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-12|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-12|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/so-storony-vsu-minami-120-mm-kalibra-obstrelyany-naselennye-punkty-na-donetskom-i-mariupolskom-napravlenii-daniil-bezsonov/|title=Со стороны ВСУ минами калибра 120 мм обстреляны населенные пункты на Донецком и Мариупольском направлении – Даниил Безсонов (видео) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-12|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-17|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire four times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, rocket launchers, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 82&#160;mm mortars to attack pro-Russian redoubts at Kalynove, Kalynove-Borshchevate and Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/12/operativnaya-svodka-v-lnr-obstrelyany-tri-poselka-zhertv-net-2/|title=Оперативная сводка: в ЛНР обстреляны три поселка, жертв нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-12|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 11 occasions,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/384964538662835?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 12 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-12 |accessdate=2018-06-12 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 32 ceasefire violations were registered,<ref name=MoD7am06-13>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/13/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-13-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 11 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=13 June 2018 |accessdate=13 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk|quote=Сегодня, в течение ночи 13 июня, враг 7 раз нарушал режим тишины из них 3 раза применял вооружение запрещено минского договоренностями вблизи населенных пунктов Новотошковское и Новоалександровка. Во время боев были ранены двое наших защитников. }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10150679-jfo-ukraine-reports-1-kia-2-wias-in-donbas-in-last-day.html |title=JFO: Ukraine reports 1 KIA, 2 WIAs in Donbas in last day {{!}} According to an intelligence report, an enemy armored combat vehicle was destroyed late Tuesday.|date=2018-06-13 |accessdate=2018-06-13|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, Novotroitske was hit by 120&#160;mm mortar volleys. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Marinka supported by infantry weapons. Ukrainian forces at Avdiivka, Opytne and Novotroitske, were harassed with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, 120&#160;mm mortar barrages hit Vodiane, while Hnutove came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. Lomakine, Hnutove, Shyrokyne, Pavlopil, Verkhnyotoretske, Lebedinske and Talakivka were fired at by small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. In the northern section of the demarcation line, 120&#160;mm mortar barrages struck Novotoshkivke, and 82&#160;mm mortar rounds landed in Krymske and Luhanske. Small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket propelled grenades were fired at Troitske, Zaitseve, Zolote and Stanytsia Luhanska. One Ukrainian serviceman was killed by a sniper bullet at Novhorodske. The Ukrainian military claimed that one pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicle was destroyed, and five pro-Russian fighters killed. Another four were reported wounded.<ref name=OOS-06-13/> A number of Ukrainian attacks on pro-Russian positions were recorded by pro-Russian authorities at evening. Dokuchaievsk, in the southern outskirts of Donetsk city, Ozeryanivka and Verkhnyotoretske, in the area of Horlivka, and Uzhivka, in the region of Mariupol, came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, Uzhivka was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars while Verkhnyotoretske became the target of 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk-5/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Ленинское - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-polden-vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ В полдень ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск - СЦКК / The AFU engaged Dokuchaevsk at noon – JCCC].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vnov-obstrelivayut-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ вновь обстреливают Докучаевск — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-verhnetoretskoe-nizhnee-i-ozeryanovku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Верхнеторецкое нижнее и Озеряновку - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 13 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 32 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA, 2 injured--> (including on 21 occasions in Donetsk and on 11 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-13/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-13/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 13 June eight ceasefire violations were registered, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref name=OOS-06-13/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian soldier was killed and two others were injured in the Donbass region on 12 June.<ref name=OOS-06-13>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/13/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-13-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 13 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 13 June 2018 |date=13 June 2018 |accessdate=13 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 14:18 13/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported nine Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in eight different locations using small arms, snipers, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled guns. One pro-Russian soldier was killed and two civilians were wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-proshedshie-sutki-ot-obstrela-vsu-postradali-dvoe-grazhdan-respubliki-stskk/|title=За прошедшие сутки от обстрела ВСУ пострадали двое граждан Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-13|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-13|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrelov-so-storony-vsu-povrezhdeny-doma-liniya-elektroperedach-pogib-odin-voennosluzhashhij-dnr-daniil-bezsonov/|title=В результате обстрелов со стороны ВСУ повреждены дома, линия электропередач, погиб один военнослужащий ДНР — Даниил Безсонов (видео) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-13|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-17|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local authorities, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire four times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to engage pro-Russian redoubts at Kalynove, Sokolniki, Lohvynove and Donetskyi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/13/operativnaya-svodka-v-lnr-obstrelyany-chetyre-poselka/|title=Оперативная сводка: в ЛНР обстреляны четыре поселка|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-13|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 14 occasions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/385613298597959 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 13 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-13 |accessdate=2018-06-13 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 33, total four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, 82&#160;mm mortar volleys fired from Spartak struck Avdiivka, while infantry weapons and rocket launchers were used to harass Ukrainian positions at Verkhnyotoretske and Marinka. Sniper fire was reported at Krasnohorivka. Hours later, Novotroitske was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars firing from Dokuchaievsk. In the region of Mariupol, Ukrainian redoubts at Vodiane were engaged by 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured fighting vehicles and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Talakivka was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars. Ukrainian troops at Hnutove, Pavlopil, Shyrokyne and Lebedinske became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, 122&#160;mm self-propelled guns firing from Holubovske pounded Ukrainian positions at Novotoshkivke. Novozvanivka was meanwhile struck by 120&#160;mm mortar fire, and 82&#160;mm mortar rounds landed in Novooleksandrivka and Novotoshkivke. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian forces at Yuzhne, Hladosove, Zolote, Zaitseve and Luhanske, supported by infantry weapons.<ref name=MoD7am06-14>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/14/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-14-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 14 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=14 June 2018 |accessdate=14 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10152188-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-4-wias-amid-33-enemy-attacks.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 4 WIAs amid 33 enemy attacks {{!}} According to an intelligence report, one occupier was killed and five others - wounded.|date=2018-06-14 |accessdate=2018-06-14|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-14" /> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces had broken the ceasefire on multiple occasions by evening. Spartak, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Zaitseve, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Pikuzy and Uzhivka, came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, Ukrainian tanks from Talakivka launched an attack on pro-Russian redoubts at Pikuzy; the same area was shelled by 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Uzhivka was hit by 120&#160;mm mortar volleys. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Avdiivka and Starohnativka opened fire on pro-Russian positions at Spartak and Novolaspa. Zaitseve became the target of 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-leninskoe-i-kominternovo-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Ленинское и Коминтерново - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-spartaku-stskk-3/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Спартаку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-kominternovo-2/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Коминтерново].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-novuyu-laspu-iz-bmp-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливали Новую Ласпу из БМП - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-zajtsevo-stskk-2/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Зайцево — СЦКК].</ref>

=== 14 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 33 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-14/><!--4 WIA--> (including on 21 occasions in Donetsk region and on 12 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-14/>); the fire was returned on 21 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-14/> By morning of 14 June several ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref name=OOS-06-14/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 13 June.<ref name=OOS-06-14>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/14/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-14-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 14 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 14 June 2018|date=14 June 2018 |accessdate=14 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:17 14/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported seven Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in five different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles and tanks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-primenili-po-territorii-respubliki-160-boepripasov-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ применили по территории Республики 160 боеприпасов — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-14|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-14|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Officials from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded five Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Kalynivka and Donetskyi using heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/14/operativnaya-svodka-v-lnr-obstrelyany-tri-poselka-zhertv-net-3/|title=Оперативная сводка: в ЛНР обстреляны три поселка, жертв нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-14|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian military had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/386346598524629?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 14 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-14 |accessdate=2018-06-14 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 33 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, two Ukrainian servicemen were killed and six were wounded. In the environs of Donetsk city, Avdiivka and Opytne came under 82&#160; mortar fire; nearby Krasnohorivka became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. In the region of Mariupol, heavy shelling was reported at Bohdanivka and Lebedinske, which were shelled with 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Vodiane was also hit by 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm artillery. Ukrainian forces at Pavlopil were engaged by armoured fighting vehicles supported by small arms fire. Talakivka, Hnutove and Shyrokyne were struck by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and rocket propelled grenades. In the northern section of the demarcation line, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar volleys and 122&#160;mm artillery barrages hit Novotoshkivke. Pro-Russian tanks from Holubovske launched a sustained attack on Ukrainian redoubts at the same area. Luhanske, Troitske, Orekhove and Yuzhne were also the target of 82&#160;mm and 120&#160; mm mortars.<ref name="MoD_1230-06-15_uk" /> Multiple ceasefire violations by Ukrainian forces were reported by pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city. The Ukrainian military attacked Dokuchaievsk, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Gagarin mining complex and Zaitseve, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka, Uzhivka, Petrovske, Styla and Pikuzy. In the main incidents, 120&#160;mm mortar barrages hit Uzhivka, Petrovske and Sakhanka. Pikuzy and Sakhanka were also shelled with 82&#160;mm mortars. Ukrainian tanks from Bohdanivka engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Styla, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novotroitske riddled pro-Russian defences at Dokuchaievsk with 30&#160;mm gunfire. BMP-1 armoured vehicles shelled Gagarin coal mine supported by automatic grenade launchers.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-leninskoe-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Ленинское - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-stskk-7/ ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-petrovskomu-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Петровскому - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-sahanke-dokuchaevsku-i-leninskomu-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Саханке, Докучаевску и Ленинскому - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-leninskoe-kominternovo-i-gorlovku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Ленинское, Коминтерново и Горловку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-stylu-i-sahanku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают Стылу и Саханку - СЦКК].</ref> Heavy shelling was reported at Kirovsk, within the boundaries of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/14/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-territorii-lnr-srazu-posle-chempionata-mira/|title=Срочно! ВСУ открыли огонь по территории ЛНР сразу после открытия чемпионата мира|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-14|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 15 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 33 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--2 KIA, 6 WIA--><ref name="MoD7am06-15">{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/15/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-15-chervnya-2018-roku/|title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 15 червня 2018 року|date=15 June 2018|publisher=MoD|language=uk|trans-title=|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref> (including on 26 occasions in Donetsk and on 7 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-06-15_uk/>); the fire was returned on 16 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-06-15_uk/> By morning of 15 June ten ceasefire violations were registered.<ref name=MoD_1230-06-15_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were killed and another six were wounded in the Donbass region on 14 June.<ref name=MoD_1230-06-15_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/15/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-06-15 |accessdate=2018-06-15 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 12 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in seven different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles, tanks and 152&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. One civilian resident was wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-vypustili-po-territorii-respubliki-bolee-270-boepripasov-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ выпустили по территории Республики более 270 боеприпасов — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-15|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-16|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same report says that Ukrainian forces committed 52 ceasefire violations over the past week. They fired eleven shells from 152&#160;mm and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery, 200 shells from 120&#160;mm and 82&#160;mm mortars, nine tank rounds and 183 shots from armoured fighting vehicles and armoured personnel carriers on the same period. Two pro-Russian soldiers were killed and another wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/15/vsu-za-nedelyu-obstrelyali-poryadka-40-naselennyh-punktov-dnr/|title=ВСУ за неделю обстреляли порядка 40 населенных пунктов ДНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-17|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire four times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian forces attacked pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Kalynivka and Donetskyi using heavy machine guns, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/14/operativnaya-svodka-v-lnr-obstrelyany-tri-poselka-zhertv-net-3/|title=Оперативная сводка: в ЛНР обстреляны три поселка, жертв нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-16|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 15 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/387052908453998 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 15 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-15 |accessdate=2018-06-15 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 36,<ref name=MoD7am06-16>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/16/zvedennya-pres-czentru-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-7-ranku-16-chervnya-2018-roku// |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 16 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=16 June 2018 |accessdate=16 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10154876-jfo-ukraine-reports-36-enemy-attacks-in-last-day.html |title=JFO: Ukraine reports 36 enemy attacks in last day {{!}} Units of Ukraine's Joint Forces delivered an adequate rebuff, suppressing the enemy activity.|date=2018-06-16 |accessdate=2018-06-16|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> one Ukrainian soldier was wounded. in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Ukrainian troops Avdiivka and Marinka became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, Bohdanivka, Vodiane, Lebedinske and Talakivka were shelled with 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Hnutove, while infantry weapons and grenade launchers were used to harass Ukrainian forces at Pavlopil, Shyrokyne, Talakivka, Vodiane, Lebedinske Hnutove and Chermalyk. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian positions near Luhanske, while 82&#160;mm mortar rounds landed in Novotoshkivke and Troitske. Separatist forces opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Svitlodarsk, Luhanske, Novhorodske, Zaitseve, Novotoshkivke and Troitske using small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Hours later,larmoured fighting vehicles launched attacks on Ukrainian positions at Zaitseve, Novotoshkivke and Zolote.<ref name=OOS-06-16/> Pro-Russian officials told the press that Ukrainian forces had broken the ceasefire on several occasions by evening. Dokuchaievsk and Kruta Balka, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Zaitseve and Dolomitne in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka, Pikuzy and Nova Tavrya came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, Pikuzy and Nova Tavrya came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire, while 82&#160;mm mortars were employed to shell Dolomitne, Kruta Balka and Sakhanka. BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Vodiane and Novoluhanske engaged pro-Russian positions at Pikuzy and Dolomitne, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novotroitske raked pro-Russian redoubts at Pikuzy with 30&#160;mm gunfire. Two civilian residents were wounded.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/utrom-zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-kominternovo-i-novoj-tavrii-stskk/ Утром зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Коминтерново и Новой Таврии - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-kominternovo-povrezhdeny-tr-doma-po-ul-ahmatovoj-stskk/ В Коминтерново повреждены три дома по ул. Ахматовой - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-stskk-4/ ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-zajtsevo-vnov-ranen-mirnyj-zhitel-prihodko/ В Зайцево вновь ранен мирный житель - Иван Приходько].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-stskk-8/ ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-dolomitnoe-sahanku-i-krutuyu-balku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливали Доломитное, Саханку и Крутую Балку - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 16 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 36 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-16/><!--1 WIA--> (including on 24 occasions in Donetsk region and on 12 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-16/>); the fire was returned on 15 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-16/> By morning of 16 June (as of 9:00&nbsp;am) ten ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned on five occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-16/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in the Donbass region on 15 June.<ref name=OOS-06-16>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/16/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-16-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 16 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 16 June 2018|date=16 June 2018 |accessdate=16 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 14:01 16/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded nine Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in eight different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless guns, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-narushili-peremirie-9-raz-raneny-mirnye-zhiteli-povrezhdeny-doma-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ нарушили перемирие 9 раз, ранены мирные жители, повреждены дома — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-16|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-16|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on three occasions within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Kalynove and Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/16/operativnaya-svodka-lnr-tri-narusheniya-rezhima-prekrashheniya-ognya-obstrelyany-dva-poselka/|title=Оперативная сводка ЛНР: три нарушения режима прекращения огня, обстреляны два поселка|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-16|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 13 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/387858965040059?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 16 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-16 |accessdate=2018-06-16 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 27 ceasefire violations were registered, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the area of Donetsk city, separatist forces opened fire on Ukrainian troops at Marinka, Krasnohorivka, Avdiivka and Verkhnyotoretske with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian tanks from Sosnovske launched an attack on Ukrainian redoubts at Pavlopil supported by 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar fire. Novohryhorivka was shelled by armoured fighting vehicles, while Ukrainian positions at Talakivka, Hnutove, Chermalyk, Shyrokyne, Vodiane, Lebedinske and Pyshchevik became the target of infantry weapons and rocket propelled grenades. In the northern section of the demarcation line, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Zolote, while nearby Troitske came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire. Novotoshkivke was hit by 82&#160;mm mortar rounds. Zaitseve and Stanytsia Luhanska were fired at by small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-17>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/17/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-17-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 17 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=17 June 2018 |accessdate=17 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10155404-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-2-wia-s-amid-27-enemy-attacks.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 2 WIA's amid 27 enemy attacks {{!}} According to an intelligence report, one occupier has been killed for the past day.|date=2018-06-17 |accessdate=2018-06-17|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.5.ua/regiony/voroh-obstriliav-pavlopil-iz-minometiv-i-tanka-motuzianyk-171859.html|title=Ворог обстріляв Павлопіль із мінометів і танка – Мотузяник|work=5 канал|access-date=2018-06-17|language=uk-UA}}</ref> A number of Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire were reported by pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city throughout the day. Abakumove coal mine and Dokuchaievsk, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, and in the region of Mariupol, Bela Kamianka, Styla and Pikuzy came under fire. In the main incidents, Dokuchaievsk was hit by 82&#160;mm mortar rounds, while BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Nikolaevka and Talakivka engaged pro-Russian forces at Styla and Pikuzy. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novohryhorivka riddled separatists positions at Bela Kamianka with 30&#160;mm gunfire.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/utrom-vsu-obstrelyali-beluyu-kamenku-stskk/ Утром ВСУ обстреляли Белую Каменку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-style-i-dokuchaevsku-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Стыле и Докучаевску - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-shahtu-abakumova-v-donetske-i-kominternovo-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливали шахту им. Абакумова в Донецке и Коминтерново - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 17 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 27 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--2 WIAs--><ref name=MoD7am06-17/> (including on 19 occasions in Donetsk and on 7 occasions in Luhansk region);<!--19+7=26--><ref name=OOS-06-17/> the fire was returned on 9 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-17/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 16 June.<ref name=OOS-06-17>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/17/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-17-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 17 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 17 June 2018 |date=17 June 2018 |accessdate=17 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:12 17/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported seven Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in six different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-sem-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ семь раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-17|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-17|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire three times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian redoubts at Kalynove and Donetskyi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.donetsk.kp.ru/online/news/3147834/|title=Украинские войска выпустили по ЛНР 40 боеприпасов|last=правды»|first=Павел ХАНАРИН {{!}} Сайт «Комсомольской|date=2018-06-17|work=KP.RU - сайт «Комсомольской правды»|access-date=2018-06-17|language=ru}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops once, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/388604864965469 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 17 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-17 |accessdate=2018-06-17 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 20, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded at [[Krymske, Novoaidar Raion|Krymske]]. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Pisky came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire, while Ukrainian positions at Avdiivka were hit by heavy machine gun fire and antitank rockets. In the region of Mariupol, heavy shelling was reported at Starohnativka, which was struck by 120&nbsp;mm mortar barrages fired from Novolaspa. The separatists employed heavy machine guns and grenade launchers to harass Ukrainian troops at Pyshchevik, Shyrokyne, Hnutove, Vodiane and Lebedinske. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Krymske and Novotoshkivke became the target of 120&#160;mm mortars firing from Zholobok. Some hours later, Krymske was also shelled from 82&#160;mm mortars. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian forces at Hladosove supported by small arms and heavy machine gun fire.<ref name=MoD7am06-18>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/18/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-18-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 18 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=18 June 2018 |accessdate=18 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10155935-jfo-ukraine-reports-1-wia-amid-20-enemy-attacks.html |title=JFO: Ukraine reports 1 WIA amid 20 enemy attacks {{!}} According to intelligence reports, five occupiers were wounded in the last day.|date=2018-06-18 |accessdate=2018-06-18|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref><ref name=OOS-06-18/> In the self-styled Donetsk People's Republic, pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces had broken the ceasefire on two occasions by evening, one around Donetsk city and another in the region of Mariupol. BMP-1 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk from Mykolaevka, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Starohnativka opened fire at Novolaspa.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-i-novolaspu-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск и Новоласпу — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-17|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-17|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The Press Center of the [[Ministry of Defence (Ukraine)|Ministry of Defense]] reported that three Ukrainian soldiers were killed and another twenty-five were wounded in action during the 24th week (11–18 June) of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/en/news/2018/06/18/briefing-ministry-of-defence-of-ukraine-spokesperson-on-frontline-situation/ |title=Briefing Ministry of Defence of Ukraine spokesperson on frontline situation |date=18 June 2018 |accessdate=4 July 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref>

=== 18 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 20 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-18/><!--1 WIA--> (including on 16 occasions in Donetsk region and on 4 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-18/>); the fire was returned on 9 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-18/> By morning of 18 June two ceasefire violations were registered.<ref name=OOS-06-18/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in the Donbass region on 17 June.<ref name=OOS-06-18>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/18/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-18-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 18 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 18 June 2018|date=18 June 2018 |accessdate=18 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:19 18/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported three Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in three locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-territorii-respubliki-po-dvum-napravleniyam-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли территории Республики по двум направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-18|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref> In the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic, local officials reported three Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire. The Ukrainian military used heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&#160;mm mortars and 152&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery to pound pro-Russian positions at Donetskyi, Zholobok and Lohvynove. A civilian residence and a farm were destroyed at Zholobok. One female civilian was wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/18/operativnaya-svodka-komandovaniya-lnr-obstrelyany-logvinovo-i-donetskij/|title=Оперативная сводка командования ЛНР: обстреляны Логвиново и Донецкий|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/18/v-lnr-prizvali-obse-zafiksirovat-prisutstvie-zapreshhennyh-vooruzhenij-vsu-i-dobitsya-ih-otvoda/|title=В ЛНР призвали ОБСЕ зафиксировать присутствие запрещенных вооружений ВСУ и добиться их отвода|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/22/vsu-vypustili-po-territorii-respubliki-bolee-140-snaryadov-nm-lnr/|title=ВСУ выпустили по территории республики более 140 снарядов – НМ ЛНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 4 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/389535201539102 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 18 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-18 |accessdate=2018-06-18 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 28 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the surroundings of Donetsk city, 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds hit Verkhnyotoretske. The separatists fired small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers at Ukrainian troops near Avdiivka, Marinka, Opytne and Kamianka. Sniper fire was reported at Krasnohorivka. In the region of Mariupol, Lebedinske and Starohnativka were shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars; Chermalyk was meanwhile hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds. Hnutove, Vodiane, Shyrokyne and Chermalyk became the target of infantry weapons and grenade launchers. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Troitske was hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds, while 82&nbsp;mm mortars were fired at Novotoshkivke. Separatist forces fired small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers at Yuzhne, Hladosove, Zaitseve and Luhanske.<ref name=MoD7am06-19>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/19/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-19-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 19 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=19 June 2018 |accessdate=19 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10157393-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-2-wia-s-amid-28-enemy-attacks.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 2 WIA's amid 28 enemy attacks {{!}} According to intelligence reports, one enemy armored combat vehicle and a GAZ-66 truck were destroyed.|date=2018-06-19 |accessdate=2018-06-19|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported by evening that Ukrainian forces had attacked Zaitseve, north of Horlivka, with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-zajtsevo-stskk-3/|title=Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Зайцево — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-18|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref> It was later disclosed that Novolaspa, in the region of Mariupol, was hit by 120&#160;mm mortar volleys, while Dokuchaievsk, in the southern outskirts of Donetsk city, became the target of infantry weapons and automatic grenade launchers.<ref name=":16" /> Colonel Andryi Marochko, military spokesman of the self-proclaimed Luhansk Peoples Republic, told the press that the last civilian resident at Zholobok had been evacuated after his home was destroyed by 152&#160;mm artillery rounds. The rest of the civilians had abandoned the village in the summer of 2017, after a Ukrainian attempt to take over the site.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/18/v-hode-obstrela-unichtozhen-dom-poslednej-zhitelnitsy-n-p-zhelobok-v-lnr/|title=В ходе обстрела уничтожен дом последней жительницы н.п. Желобок в ЛНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 19 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 28 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--2 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-19/> (including on 21 occasions in Donetsk and on 7 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-19/>); the fire was returned on 16 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-19/> By morning of 19 June at least five ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned on several occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-19/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 18 June.<ref name=OOS-06-19>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/19/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-19-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 19 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 19 June 2018 |date=19 June 2018 |accessdate=19 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 12:59 19/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city said that there were four Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in three locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars and 120&#160;mm mortars.<ref name=":16">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-territorii-dnr-po-dvum-napravleniyam-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли территории ДНР по двум направлениям — СЦКК / AFU shelled the DPR territory in two directions – JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-19|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-20|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local authorities, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire two times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Hristove and Krasnyi Yar employing heavy machine guns, [[GP-25|under-barrel grenade launchers]] and BMP-2 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/19/operativnaya-svodka-po-lnr-obstrelyany-poselki-hristovoe-i-krasnyj-yar/|title=Оперативная сводка по ЛНР: обстреляны поселки Христовое и Красный Яр|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-20|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 4 occasions, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in action.<ref name=FB_6pm_06-19>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/390378748121414 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 19 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-19 |accessdate=2018-06-19 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 26, as a result, another two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Verkhnyotoretske, Vodiane, Marinka, Taramchuk, Novoselivka and Avdiivka were fired at from small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, Ukrainian positions at Talakivka were engaged with grenade launchers, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured fighting vehicles and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns; 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys also struck Chermalyk. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles from Novolaspa launched an attack on Starohnativka supported by 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Separatist forces opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Pavlopil, Vodiane, Shyrokyne and Lebedinske using infantry weapons and rocket launchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Ukrainian forces at Novhorodske were engaged with ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns, while Artemove and Troitske were attacked with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-20>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/20/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-20-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 20 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=20 June 2018 |accessdate=20 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10158818-donbas-update-3-wias-as-militants-violate-ceasefire-in-all-sectors.html |title=Donbas update: 3 WIAs as militants violate ceasefire in all sectors {{!}} The intensity of hostilities decreased overnight Wednesday. |date=2018-06-20 |accessdate=2018-06-20|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials reported several Ukrainian violations of the truce by evening. Shyroka Balka and Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka and, in the region of Mariupol, Novolaspa and Bela Kamianka, came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, BMP-2 armoured fighting vehicles from Starohnativka and Novhorodske opened fire on pro-Russian positions at Bela Kamianka, Novolaspa and Shyroka Balka. Intense mortar fire was also reported at Bela Kamianka, which was hit by 120&#160;mm volleys. Gagarin mining complex was shelled with 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-beloj-kamenke-stskk/|title=Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Белой Каменке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-19|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-20|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-ryad-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk-3/|title=ВСУ обстреляли ряд населенных пунктов Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-19|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-20|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 20 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 26 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-20/><!--3 WIA--> (including on 23 occasions in Donetsk region and on 3 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-20/>); the fire was returned on 16 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-20/> By morning of 20 June (as of 9:00&nbsp;am) three ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned.<ref name=OOS-06-20/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 19 June.<ref name=OOS-06-20>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/20/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-20-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 20 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 20 June 2018|date=20 June 2018 |accessdate=20 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 14:21 20/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported six Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in four different locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-primenili-po-territorii-respubliki-152-edinitsy-boepripasov-stskk/|title=ВСУ применили по территории Республики 152 единицы боеприпасов – СЦКК / AFU fired 152 rounds on the territory of the Republic – JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-20|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-20|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire four times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed heavy machine guns, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars to engage pro-Russian redoubts at Zheleznaya Roshcha and Donetskyi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/20/operativnaya-svodka-v-lnr-obstrelyany-poselki-zelenaya-roshha-i-donetskij/|title=Оперативная сводка: в ЛНР обстреляны поселки Зеленая Роща и Донецкий|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-20|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening no casualties on the Ukrainian side by 6:00&nbsp;pm amidst several registered ceasefire violations by the pro-Russian military.<!--it says 7am-8pm 3 violations, not clear, are the ones reported in the morning (3) counted or not--><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/391278518031437?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 20 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-20 |accessdate=2018-06-20 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 30 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. In the environs of Donetsk city, Verkhnyotoretske, Pisky, Avdiivka and Kamianka became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, Vodiane was shelled with 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars firing from Pikuzy. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles attacked Ukrainian positions at Bohdanivka. Separatist forces opened fire on Ukrainian troops at Pavlopil, Bohdanivka, Vodiane, Hnutove, Lebedinske, Pyshchevik and Shyrokyne with infantry weapons and grenade launchers. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Novotoshkivke was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery. Novoaleksandrivka, Svitlodarsk, Zolote, Katerinivka, Yuzhne, Troitske and Luhanske were hit by small arms fire, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-21>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/21/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-21-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 21 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=21 June 2018 |accessdate=21 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10160375-joint-forces-in-donbas-respond-to-militant-shelling-by-suppressing-enemy-firing-positions.html |title=Joint Forces in Donbas respond to militant shelling by suppressing enemy firing positions {{!}} Three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action in the past day.|date=2018-06-21 |accessdate=2018-06-21|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-21" /> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported heavy shelling on several locations along the demarcation line throughout the day. Yasynuvata and Vasiilivka, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka, and Uzhivka, in the region of Mariupol, came under intense fire. In the main incidents, Donetsk water purification plant was once again attacked by Ukrainian forces; the workers had to take cover in shelters. Pro-Russian positions at Vasiilivka were repeatedly hit by 82&#160;mm mortar barrages; 82&#160;mm mortars were also fired at Uzhivka and Gagarin mining complex. One civilian resident was wounded.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-obekty-vodosnabzheniya-v-yasinovatskom-rajone-minstroj/ ВСУ обстреляли объекты водоснабжения в Ясиноватском районе – Минстрой / AFU shelled water-supply facilities in Yasinovatsky district – Ministry of Construction Industry].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-vasilevku-iz-minometov-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Васильевку из минометов - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-leninskoe-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Ленинское — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-gorlovke-stskk-2/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Горловке - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-gorlovke-ranen-mirnyj-zhitel-prihodko/ В Горловке ранен мирный житель].</ref>

=== 21 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 30 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--3 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-21/> (including on 20 occasions in Donetsk and on 10 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-21/>); the fire was returned on 12 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-21/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 21 June four ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref name=OOS-06-21/>) The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 20 June.<ref name=OOS-06-21>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/21/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-21-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 21 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 21 June 2018 |date=21 June 2018 |accessdate=21 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:26 21/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city said that there were five Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in three locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and 120&nbsp;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-territoriyu-respubliki-po-trem-napravleniyam-ranen-mirnyj-zhitel-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли территорию Республики по трем направлениям, ранен мирный житель — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-21|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-21|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Officials from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded one Ukrainian violation of the truce when BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Novotoshkivke engaged pro-Russian positions at Donetskyi supported by 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mil-lnr.info/press-sluzhba/svodka/item/2839-operativnaya-svodka-za-sutki-s-20-na-21-iyunya|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 20 на 21 июня|access-date=2018-06-21|language=ru-ru}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 3 occasions from 7:00&nbsp;am to 6:00&nbsp;pm, all in the area of Mariupol, with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref name=FB_6pm_06-21>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/392084584617497 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 21 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-21 |accessdate=2018-06-21 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 29, as a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded by a [[Fragmentation (weaponry)|shrapnel]]. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Avdiivka, Krasnohorivka, Pisky and Marinka became the target of infantry weapons and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns fired at Hnutove, while Starohnativka was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Ukrainian troops at Shyrokyne, Lebedinske, Pavlopil, Novohryhorivka, Vodiane and Chermalyk were harassed with small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and rocket propelled grenades. In the northern section of the demarcation line, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys landed in Novotoshkivke. Small arms, heavy machine guns and antitank rockets were also fired at Ukrainian positions around Troitske, Zalizne, Zaitseve and Stanytsia Luhanska.<ref name=MoD7am06-22>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/22/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-22-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 22 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=22 June 2018 |accessdate=22 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10161836-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-1-wia-amid-29-enemy-attacks.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 1 WIA amid 29 enemy attacks {{!}} According to intelligence reports, the enemy suffered losses in the last day: three occupiers were killed and three others were wounded.|date=2018-06-22 |accessdate=2018-06-22|publisher=UNIAN}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported a number of attacks on their forces throughout the day. The Ukrainian army opened fire at Holmivsky, in the area of Horlivka, and at Pikuzy and Novolaspa, in the region of Mariupol. In the main incidents, heavy shelling was witnessed at Pikuzy, which was hit by several artillery barrages fired from Talakivka by 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns. BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Zaitseve supported by 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles and automatic grenade launchers attacked pro-Russian positions at Holmivsky. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Starohnativka riddled pro-Russian redoubts at Novolaspa with 30&nbsp;mm gunfire. One civilian resident was wounded.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-kominternovo-stskk-3/ ВСУ обстреляли Коминтерново - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-novolaspu-i-kominternovo-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Новоласпу и Коминтерново - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-kominternovo-ranen-mirnyj-zhitel-stskk/ В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ Коминтерново ранен мирный житель - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-golmovskij-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Гольмовский - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 22 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 29 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-22/><!--1 WIA--> (including on 21 occasions in Donetsk region and on 10 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-22/>)<!--21+10=31, perhaps something to do with targeted and not targeted attacks-->; the fire was returned on 14 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-22/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 22 June six ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned on several occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-22/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in the Donbass region on 21 June.<ref name=OOS-06-22>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/22/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-22-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 22 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 22 June 2018|date=22 June 2018 |accessdate=22 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:04 22/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded five Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in four different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless guns, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns. One civilian resident was confirmed wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-ispolzovali-protiv-respubliki-artilleriyu-i-vooruzhenie-bronetehniki-stskk/|title=ВСУ использовали против Республики артиллерию и вооружение бронетехники — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-22|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same sources recorded 39 Ukrainian violations of the truce over the past week. The Ukrainian military fired 37 rounds from 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery, 138 shells from 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars and some 500 rounds from armoured fighting vehicles. Three civilians were wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/22/vsu-za-nedelyu-pochti-40-raz-narushili-rezhim-tishiny-bezsonov/|title=ВСУ за неделю почти 40 раз нарушили режим тишины — Безсонов|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire three times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 120&nbsp;mm mortars to shell pro-Russian positions at Donetskyi and Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/22/vsu-trizhdy-obstrelyali-territoriyu-lnr-za-sutki/|title=ВСУ трижды обстреляли территорию ЛНР за сутки|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 7 occasions from 7:00 am to 6:00 pm, with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/393170571175565 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 22 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-22 |accessdate=2018-06-22 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 27 ceasefire violations were registered. Pro-Russian forces opened fire on Ukrainian troops at Verkhnyotoretske, Avdiivka, Marinka, Kamianka and Pisky with small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. In the region of Mariupol, 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery shelled Hnutove and Vodiane. Lebedinske and Talakivka were meanwhile hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles from Bela Kamianka engaged Ukrainian positions at Starohnativka. Pavlopil, Pishchevik and Shyrokyne became the target of infantry weapons and rocket launchers. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Novotoshkivke was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery. The separatists attacked Ukrainian positions at Zalizne, Luhanske, Troitske and Zaitseve with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-23>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/23/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-23-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 23 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=23 June 2018 |accessdate=23 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-defense/2486088-militants-violated-ceasefire-in-eastern-ukraine-27-times-in-last-day.html |title=Militants violated ceasefire in eastern Ukraine 27 times in last day|date=2018-06-23 |accessdate=2018-06-23|publisher=[[Ukrinform]]}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city recorded a number of attacks on their troops throughout the day. Horlivka, Zaitseve and Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka, and Sakhanka, in the region of Mariupol, came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, Sakhanka was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars, while Gagarin mining complex was attacked by BMP-1 armoured vehicles supported by automatic grenade launchers. Heavy fire was reported at Horlivka, where several civilian residences were hit by mortar rounds.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-zajtsevo-stskk-4/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Зайцево - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-gorlovku-iz-bmp-i-granatometov-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливали Горловку из БМП и гранатометов - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-sahanku-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Саханку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-gorlovki-povrezhdeny-neskolko-domostroenij-stskk/ В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ Горловки повреждены несколько домостроений - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 23 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 27 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref name=MoD7am06-23/> (including on 20 occasions in Donetsk and on 7 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-23/>); the fire was returned on 17 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-23/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 23 June nine ceasefire violations were registered, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref name=OOS-06-23/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 22 June.<ref name=OOS-06-23>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/23/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-23-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 23 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 23 June 2018 |date=23 June 2018 |accessdate=23 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:15 23/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported five Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in four locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120 mmmortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-primenili-po-territorii-respubliki-54-boepripasa/|title=За сутки ВСУ применили по территории Республики 54 боеприпаса {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-23|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Local authorities announced that the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire on two occasions within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. Ukrainian forces from Krymske and Novotoshkivke used 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Donetskyi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/23/operativnaya-svodka-v-lnr-obstrelyan-poselok-donetskij/|title=Оперативная сводка: в ЛНР обстрелян поселок Донецкий|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on eight occasions between 7:00&nbsp;am and 6:00&nbsp;pm, another two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/394111891081433 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 23 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-23 |accessdate=2018-06-23 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 25, as a result, total five Ukrainian servicemen were wounded. Around Donetsk city, 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys struck Kamianka. Avdiivka, Pisky, Kamianka and Novoselivka became the target of infantry weapons and rocket launchers. In the region of Mariupol, 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns pounded Ukrainian positions at Vodiane, Lebedinske and Talakivka. Pro-Russian forces fired small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers at Pavlopil, Shyrokyne and Lebedinske. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, pro-Russian forces attacked Krymske and Novotoshkivke with 82&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured fighting vehicles and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery. Ukrainian positions at Zolote, Zaitseve, Svitlodarsk, Novhorodske, Novotoshkivke and Krymske were hit by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and antitank rockets.<ref name=MoD7am06-24>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/24/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-24-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 24 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=24 June 2018 |accessdate=24 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10163612-jfo-ukraine-reports-5-wia-s-amid-25-enemy-attacks.html |publisher=UNIAN|title=JFO: Ukraine reports 5 WIA's amid 25 enemy attacks {{!}} According to intelligence reports, the enemy suffered losses in the last day: three occupiers were killed and four others were wounded.|date=2018-06-24 |accessdate=2018-06-24}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-24" /> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces had broken the ceasefire on multiple occasions by evening. Dokuchaievsk, in the environs of Donetsk city, Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Pikuzy, Sakhanka, Uzhivka and Novolaspa, came under attack. In the main incidents, Dokuchaievsk and Sakhanka were shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars; heavy shelling was also reported at Uzhivka, which came under 122&nbsp;mm artillery fire. Ukrainian infantry attempting to slip through the demarcation line at Pikuzy was met by heavy fire from pro-Russian positions and driven back with casualties. BMP-2 armoured fighting vehicles from Shyrokyne engaged pro-Russian forces at Sakhanka. One civilian resident was wounded at Dokuchaievsk.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-kominternovo-ukrainskie-boeviki-ponesli-sushhestvennye-poteri/ Под Коминтерново украинские боевики понесли существенные потери].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/utrom-vsu-obstrelyali-leninskoe-stskk-2/ Утром ВСУ обстреляли Ленинское - СЦКК и МО ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-sovershili-obstrel-dokuchaevska-stskk/ ВСУ совершили обстрел Докучаевска, ранена мирная жительница - СЦКК и МО ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-v-ocherednoj-raz-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-stskk-2/ ВСУ в очередной раз обстреляли Докучаевск - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-gorlovku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Горловку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-novolaspe-i-sahanke-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Новоласпе и Саханке - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 24 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 25 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-24/><!--5 WIA--> (including on 14 occasions in Donetsk region and on 11 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-24/>); the fire was returned on 11 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-24/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that five Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 23 June.<ref name=OOS-06-24>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/24/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-24-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 22 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 24 June 2018|date=24 June 2018 |accessdate=24 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:50 24/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded eight Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in six different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless guns, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-primenyali-protiv-respubliki-gaubitsy-i-minomety-stskk/|title=ВСУ применяли против Республики гаубицы и минометы — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-24|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-24|language=ru-RU}}</ref> No violations of the ceasefire were reported by authorities of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/24/vsu-perebrosili-v-zonu-oos-tanki-i-gaubitsy-nm-lnr/|title=ВСУ перебросили в зону "ООС" танки и гаубицы — НМ ЛНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-24|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that from 7:00&nbsp;am to 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian military had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 5 occasions, as a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/394998590992763 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 24 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-24 |accessdate=2018-06-24 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10163987-donbas-update-one-ukrainian-soldier-wounded-amid-five-enemy-attacks-on-june-24.html |title=Donbas update: One Ukrainian soldier wounded amid five enemy attacks on June 24 {{!}} In the daytime, the situation escalated in the Mariupol sector.|publisher=UNIAN|date=2018-06-25 |accessdate=2018-06-25}}</ref> By the end of the day total 22 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was killed, four were wounded. In the surroundings of Donetsk city, 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds landed in Avdiivka. The separatists also fired small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers at Ukrainian positions in Avdiivka, Marinka and Kamianka. In the region of Mariupol, heavy shelling was reported at Vodiane. The Ukrainian stronghold was hit by several 122&nbsp;mm and 152&nbsp;mm artillery barrages; the area was also the target of 120&nbsp;mm and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Hnutove and Lebedinske were shelled by 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery, while Ukrainian forces at Bohdanivka received 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Pro-Russian tanks from Sakhanka launched a sustained attack on Lebedinske, supported by armoured fighting vehicles and infantry weapons. Hnutove, Bohdanivka, Vodiane and Shyrokyne became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. in the northern section of the demarcation line, Krymske was shelled with 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Ukrainian troops at Novozvanivka were harassed with small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and rocket propelled grenades.<ref name=MoD7am06-25>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/25/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-25-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 25 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=25 June 2018 |accessdate=25 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10164134-donbas-update-ukraine-reports-1-kia-4-wias-amid-22-enemy-attacks-in-past-day.html |title=Donbas update: Ukraine reports 1 KIA, 4 WIAs amid 22 enemy attacks in past day {{!}} The enemy employed artillery systems, mortars, grenade launchers, and small arms.|publisher=UNIAN|date=2018-06-25 |accessdate=2018-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-defense/2486983-militants-violated-ceasefire-in-eastern-ukraine-22-times-in-last-day.html |title=Militants violated ceasefire in eastern Ukraine 22 times in last day|date=2018-06-25 |accessdate=2018-06-25|publisher=Ukrinform}}</ref> Multiple Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire were reported by pro-Russian officials by evening. The Ukrainian military attacked Vasiilivka and Dokuchaievsk, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Horlivka, Gagarin mining complex, Holmivsky and Zaitseve, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Uzhivka, Novolaspa, Sakhanka, Pikuzy and Novyboeve. In the main incidents, 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery was fired at the pro-Russian stronghold of Uzhivka, while Pikuzy and Novolaspa were shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Gagarin mining complex was hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Ukrainian tanks from Talakivka launched an attack on pro-Russian redoubts at Pikuzy; tank rounds also hit Ukrainian positions at Dokuchaievsk. BMP-1 armoured fighting vehicles engaged pro-Russian forces at Novolaspa and Holmivsky.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-gorlovke-otmecheny-novye-razrusheniya-iz-za-obstrelov-vsu-ivan-prihodko/ В Горловке отмечены новые разрушения из-за обстрелов ВСУ - Иван Приходько].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-gorlovku-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Горловку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-obstrel-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk-2/ ВСУ ведут обстрел населенных пунктов Республики - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-iz-tanka-obstrelyali-kominternovo-stskk/ ВСУ из танка обстреляли Коминтерново - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-na-gorlovskom-napravlenii/ ВСУ открыли огонь на Горловском направлении].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-vasilevku-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Васильевку - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 25 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 22 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA, 4 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-25/> (including on 16 occasions in Donetsk and on 6 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-25/>); the fire was returned on 10 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-25/> By morning of 25 June four ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref name=OOS-06-25/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was killed and another four were wounded in the Donbass region on 24 June.<ref name=OOS-06-25>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/25/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-25-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 25 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 25 June 2018 |date=25 June 2018 |accessdate=25 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:01 25/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 15 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 11 locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles and tanks. One civilian was confirmed wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-territoriyu-respubliki-po-trem-napravleniyam-ranen-mirnyj-zhitel-stskk-2/|title=ВСУ обстреляли территорию Республики по трем направлениям, ранен мирный житель — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-06-25|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-06-25|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire five times within the borders of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82 mortars, 120 mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to engage pro-Russian positions at Lozove, Lohvynove, Sokolniki, Veselehorivka and Sentianivka.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/25/operativnaya-svodka-po-lnr-obstrelyany-pyat-poselkov-zhertv-net/|title=Оперативная сводка по ЛНР: обстреляны пять поселков, жертв нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-25|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on two occasions between 7:00&nbsp;am and 6:00&nbsp;pm, no casualties were reported.<ref name=FB_6pm_06-25>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/395851137574175 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 25 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-25 |accessdate=2018-06-25 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 24, as a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, 82&nbsp;mm mortar volleys struck Avdiivka and Kruta Balka. Kamianka, Marinka and Verkhnyotoretske became the target of infantry weapons and grenade launchers. Pro-Russian troops in the region of Mariupol opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Hnutove, Lebedinske, Marinka, Pavlopil, Starohnativka and Shyrokyne with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket lanchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Krymske was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars, while Ukrainian redoubts at Orekhove, Luhanske and Svitlodarsk were hit by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and antitank rockets.<ref name=MoD7am06-26>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/26/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-0700-26-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 26 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=26 June 2018 |accessdate=26 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref name=MoD7am06-26en>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/en/news/2018/06/26/situation-update-east-of-ukraine-as-of-morning-june-26-2018/ |title=Situation Update, east of Ukraine as of morning, June 26, 2018|date=26 June 2018 |accessdate=1 July 2018 |publisher=MoD}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10165532-jfo-ukraine-reports-1-wia-amid-24-enemy-attacks-in-donbas.html |publisher=UNIAN|title=JFO: Ukraine reports 1 WIA amid 24 enemy attacks in Donbas {{!}} According to intelligence reports, two occupiers were killed and another three wounded.|date=2018-06-26 |accessdate=2018-06-26}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources told the press that Ukrainian forces had broken the ceasefire on several occasions by evening. Dokuchaievsk, in the region of Donetsk, Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Styla and Petrovske, came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds hit Styla and Dokuchaievsk, while BMP-1 and BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Dzerzhinsky and Novotroitske engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Gagarin mining complex and Dokuchaievsk. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novohnativka raked Ukrainian positions at Petrovske with 30&nbsp;mm gunfire.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-veli-obstrel-gorlovki-stskk/ ВСУ вели обстрел Горловки - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-i-petrovskoe-stskk-2/ ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск и Петровское - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-stylu-i-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Стылу и Докучаевск - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 26 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 24 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-26/><ref name=MoD7am06-26en/><!--1 WIA--> (including on 16 occasions in Donetsk region and on 8 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-26/>); the fire was returned on 14 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-26/> By morning of 26 June two ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned.<ref name=OOS-06-26/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian soldier was wounded in the Donbass region on 25 June.<ref name=OOS-06-26>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/26/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-26-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 22 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 26 June 2018|date=26 June 2018 |accessdate=26 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 12:21 26/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded seven Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in five different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless guns, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-territoriyu-respubliki-po-trem-napravleniyam-poselok-kominternovo-obestochen-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли территорию Республики по трем направлениям, поселок Коминтерново обесточен - СЦКК / The AFU shelled the territory of the Republic in three directions, the village of Kominternovo was left without power – JCCC|last=|first=|date=26 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> In the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic, local officials reported three Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire. The Ukrainian military used small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured fighting vehicles to pound pro-Russian positions at Kalynove and Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/26/operativnaya-svodka-lnr-obstrelyany-kalinovo-i-lozovoe-zhertv-net/|title=Оперативная сводка ЛНР: обстреляны Калиново и Лозовое, жертв нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-26|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that from 7:00&nbsp;am to 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian military had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 5 occasions, exclusively in Luhansk region, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/396756787483610 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 26 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-26 |accessdate=2018-06-26 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 30 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was killed, two were wounded. In the ouskirts of Donetsk city, Marinka and Pisky were shelled with 82&nbsp;mm mortars, while Avdiivka was fired at from small arms, rocket launchers and ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Novoselivka. In the region of Mariupol, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar barrages hit Vodiane. The separatist also employed 82&nbsp;mm mortars to shell Lebedinske. Hnutove, Pyshchevik and Starohnativka became the target of small arms and grenade launchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery shelled Novotoshkivke, while Krymske came under 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Ukrainian forces at Zaitseve, Mayorsk, Katerinivka, Zholobok, Troitske and Lozove were attacked with infantry weapons, rocket launchers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref name=MoD7am06-27>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/27/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-07-00-27-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 27 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=27 June 2018 |accessdate=27 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10167047-ukraine-reports-1-kia-2-wias-amid-30-enemy-attacks-in-donbas-in-past-day.html|title=Ukraine reports 1 KIA, 2 WIAs amid 30 enemy attacks in Donbas in past day {{!}} According to intelligence reports, three occupiers were killed and another five wounded in battles with Ukraine's Joint Forces.|publisher=UNIAN|date=2018-06-27 |accessdate=2018-06-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-defense/2488473-militants-violated-ceasefire-in-eastern-ukraine-30-times-in-last-day.html |title=Militants violated ceasefire in eastern Ukraine 30 times in last day|date=2018-06-27 |accessdate=2018-06-27|publisher=Ukrinform}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-27" /><ref name=MoD7am06-27en>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/en/news/2018/06/27/situation-update-east-of-ukraine-as-of-morning-june-27-2018/ |title=Situation Update, east of Ukraine as of morning, June 27, 2018|date=27 June 2018 |accessdate=1 July 2018 |publisher=MoD}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported a number of Ukrainian violations of the truce by evening. Ukrainian forces attacked Dokuchaievsk, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, and, in the area of Horlivka, Zaitseve and Gagarin mining complex. BMP-2 armoured fighting vehicles from Nikolaevka opened fire on pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk, while Zaitseve and Gagarin mining complex were shelled with automatic grenade launchers, antitank rocket launchers and 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/dnem-vsu-obstrelyali-gorlovku-stskk/ Днем ВСУ обстреляли Горловку - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-iz-bmp-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск из БМП - СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-zajtsevo-stskk-5/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Зайцево - СЦКК].</ref>

=== 27 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 30 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA, 2 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-27 /><ref name=MoD7am06-27en /> (including on 17 occasions in Donetsk and on 13 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-27/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-27/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 27 June nine ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref name=OOS-06-27/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was killed and another two were wounded in the Donbass region on 26 June.<ref name=OOS-06-27>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/27/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-27-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 27 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 27 June 2018 |date=27 June 2018 |accessdate=27 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:31 27/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported three Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in three locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-tri-raza-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ три раза нарушили режим прекращения огня - СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire three times – JCCC|last=|first=|date=27 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref> According to local authorities, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire three times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian redoubts at Prishib, Sokolniki and Nyzhne Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/27/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-tri-poselka-zhertv-net/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка — обстреляны три поселка, жертв нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening pro-Russian military had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 12 occasions between 7:00&nbsp;am and 6:00&nbsp;pm, as a result, three Ukrainian servicemen were [[Killed in action|lethally wounded]]<!--три українських військовослужбовці отримали порання несумісні із життям--> at [[Bohdanivka, Volnovakha Raion|Bohdanivka]] by pro-Russian 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery; another Ukrainian soldier was wounded at [[Vodiane, Volnovakha Raion|Vodiane]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/397721127387176 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 27 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-27 |accessdate=2018-06-27 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10168421-three-ukrainian-soldiers-killed-in-122mm-artillery-attack-near-mariupol-on-wednesday.html |title=Three Ukrainian soldiers killed in 122mm artillery attack near Mariupol on Wednesday {{!}} Enemy casualties are not known yet.|publisher=UNIAN|date=2018-06-27 |accessdate=2018-06-27}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 32, another two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded, two civilians were injured by shelling in [[Zalizne]]. In the environs of Donetsk city, Marinka was shelled with 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, supported by small arms and heavy machine guns. The Ukrainian stronghold of Avdiivka was attacked by armoured fighting vehicles supported by heavy machine guns, rocket lanchers and antiaircraft guns. Small arms and heavy machine gun fire was reported at Opytne. In the region of Mariupol, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery shelled Hnutove; heavy shelling was also reported at Starohnativka, hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds. The separatists fired infantry weapons at Ukrainian positions around Shyrokyne, Talakivka, Pavlopil and Vodiane. In the northern section of the demarcation line, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Yuzhne, supported by heavy machine gun fire. Krymske was shelled with 82&nbsp;mm mortars fired from Sentianivka and Zholobok. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Luhanske, while Ukrainian troops at Stanytsia Luhanska were harassed with small arms fire.<ref name=MoD7am06-28>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/28/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-07-00-28-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 28 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=28 June 2018 |accessdate=28 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-defense/2489288-militants-violated-ceasefire-in-eastern-ukraine-32-times-in-last-day.html |publisher=Ukrinform |title=Militants violated ceasefire in eastern Ukraine 32 times in last day |date=2018-06-28 |accessdate=2018-06-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/ukrainian/news-44640247 |publisher=[[BBC Ukrainian]] |title=3 військових загинули, 3 поранені за добу на Донбасі |trans-title= |date=2018-06-28 |accessdate=2018-06-28 |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in the surroundings of Donetsk city and in the region of Mariupol by evening. BMP-1 and BMP-2 armoured fighting vehicles from Novohryhorivka launched a sustained attack on pro-Russian positions at Bela Kamianka, while Dokuchaievsk became the target of 120&nbsp;mm mortars fired from Novotroitske.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-i-beluyu-kamenku-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск и Белую Каменку - СЦКК|last=|first=|date=27 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref>

A new agreement on a new ceasefire starting on 1 July 2018 was announced in [[Minsk]], the capital of [[Belarus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10168319-trilateral-contact-group-in-minsk-announces-new-commitments-to-truce-in-donbas-from-july-1.html |title=Trilateral Contact Group in Minsk announces new commitments to truce in Donbas from July 1 {{!}} Russian's hybrid military troops should return to the contact line as sealed in the memorandum dated September 19, 2014. |publisher=UNIAN|date=2018-06-27 |accessdate=2018-06-27}}</ref>

=== 28 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 32 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-28/><!--3 KIAs, 3 WIAs--> (including on 26 occasions in Donetsk region and on 6 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-28/>); the fire was returned on more than half of the occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-28/> As of 9:00&nbsp;am of 28 June seven ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref name=OOS-06-28/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were killed and another three were wounded in the Donbass region on 27 June.<ref name=OOS-06-28>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/28/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-28-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 28 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 28 June 2018|date=28 June 2018 |accessdate=28 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:44 28/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire twice, using 120&nbsp;mm mortars and armoured fighting vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Bela Kamianka and Dokuchaievsk.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-dva-raza-narushhili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-est-razrusheniya-stskk/|title=ВСУ два раза нарушили режим прекращения огня, есть разрушения - СЦКК|last=|first=|date=28 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref> According to local sources, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire two times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, rocket launchers and automatic grenade launchers to attack pro-Russian troops at Kalynivka and Lohvynove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/28/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-dva-poselka-3/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка — обстреляны два поселка|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-06-28|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 7 occasions; two Ukrainian servicemen were killed in a skirmish that took place at [[Pivdenne (Toretsk)|Pivdenne]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/398551673970788 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 28 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-28 |accessdate=2018-06-28 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 28 ceasefire violations were registered, another two Ukrainian servicemen were killed (at [[Svitlodarsk]]<!--"у районі Світлодарської дуги"--> and in [[Avdiivka]]) and two were wounded. In the area of Donetsk city, Novotroitske was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Avdiivka, Verkhnyotoretske, Novotroitske and Marinka became the target of infantry weapons and grenade launchers. In the region of Mariupol, Pavlopil was fired at from 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery. Nearby Hnutove was hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys. The separatists fired small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers at Shyrokyne, Pavlopil, Vodiane, Lebedinske and Hnutove. In the northern section of the demarcation line, a single pro-Russian tank opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Novotoshkivke. The same area, along with Yuzhne, came under 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Both settements were also attacked by armoured fighting vehicles, supported by infantry weapons and antitank rocket launchers. Ukrainian troops at Luhanske, Novhorodske, Novozvanivka and Svitlodarsk were harassed with small arms and heavy machine gun fire.<ref name=MoD7am06-29>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/29/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-07-00-29-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 29 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=29 June 2018 |accessdate=29 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10169234-four-ukrainian-troops-killed-two-wounded-in-donbas-as-militants-mount-28-shellings-in-past-day.html |title=Four Ukrainian troops killed, two wounded in Donbas as militants mount 28 shellings in past day {{!}} Near Yuzhne, the enemy actively employed mortars, grenade launchers and heavy machine guns, to provide cover for their sniper and a sabotage group.|publisher=UNIAN|date=2018-06-29 |accessdate=2018-06-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-defense/2489668-militants-violated-ceasefire-in-eastern-ukraine-28-times-in-last-day.html |title=Militants violated ceasefire in eastern Ukraine 28 times in last day |publisher=Ukrinform |date=2018-06-29 |accessdate=2018-06-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/ukrainian/news-44653323 |publisher=BBC Ukrainian |title=Два дні до перемир'я: кількість загиблих військових зростає |trans-title= |date=2018-06-29 |accessdate=2018-06-29 |language=uk}}</ref><ref name=reu /><ref name="OOS-06-29" /> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that two assaults on their redoubts led by Ukrainian infantry and tanks and supported by 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery were met with heavy fire by pro-Russian forces at Gagarin mining complex, in the area of Horlivka. In the first engagement, Ukrainian infantry supported by 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and 122&nbsp;mm artillery attempted to seize the high ground around the Ukrainian-held village of Yuzhne ([[Pivdenne (Toretsk)|Pivdenne]]), but the push was repelled with heavy casualties. In the second attempt, Ukrainian tanks from Yuzhne launched a sustained attack on pro-Russian positions north of Gagarin, supported by 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns, in order to divert pro-Russian fire from the southern sector of the defences, where Ukrainian special forces would break through the demarcation line. The manoeuvrer was thwarted and the intruders were driven back by pro-Russian military.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vs-dnr-otbili-dve-ataki-na-gorlovskom-napravlenii-mo-dnr/|title=ВС ДНР отбили две атаки на Горловском направлении – МО ДНР|last=|first=|date=28 June 2018|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-gorlovku-stskk-3/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Горловку - СЦКК|last=|first=|date=28 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/prodolzhaetsya-tankovyj-obstrel-gorlovki-stskk/|title=Продолжается танковый обстрел Горловки - СЦКК|last=|first=|date=28 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=28 June 2018}}</ref> In the region of Mariupol and around Donetsk city, BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Starohnativka and Novotroitske riddled pro-Russian outposts at Novolaspa, Bela Kamianka and Dokuchaievsk with 30&nbsp;mm gunfire. Dokuchaievsk was also hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds. Spartak became the target of small arms, automatic grenade launchers and antitank rocket launchers.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-gorlovku-i-belokamenku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Горловку и Белокаменку - СЦКК]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-iz-bmp-i-granatometov-obstrelyali-novolaspu-stskk/ ВСУ из БМП и гранатометов обстреляли Новоласпу - СЦКК]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-stskk-5/ ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск - СЦКК]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-spartak-stskk-3/ ВСУ обстреляли Спартак - СЦКК]</ref>

=== 29 June ===
The press-centre of the JFO headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 28 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--4 KIA, 2 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am06-29/> (including on 17 occasions in Donetsk and on 11 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-29/>); the fire was returned on 19 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-29/> By morning of 29 June six ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side (as of 11:00&nbsp;am).<ref name=OOS-06-29/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that four Ukrainian servicemen were killed and two were wounded in the Donbass region on 28 June.<ref name=OOS-06-29>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/29/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-29-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 29 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information by 29 June 2018 |date=29 June 2018 |accessdate=29 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 13:11 29/06/2018}}</ref><ref name=reu>{{cite web|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-ukraine-crisis-casualties/four-ukrainian-soldiers-killed-as-fighting-flares-in-separatist-conflict-idUKKBN1JP1PN?il=0 |publisher=[[Reuters]] |title=Four Ukrainian soldiers killed as fighting flares in separatist conflict |date=2018-06-29 |accessdate=2018-06-29}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported ten Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in six locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles, tanks and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://donetsk24.su/news/ezhednevnaia-svodka-narushenii-rezhima-prekrashcheniia-ognia-za-period-s-3-00-28-iiunia-po-3-00-29-iiunia-stckk-1/|title=Ежедневная сводка нарушений режима прекращения огня за период с 3:00 28 июня по 3:00  29 июня - СЦКК|last=24|first=Донецк|website=Донецк 24|language=Russian|access-date=2018-07-08}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported that Ukrainian BMP-1 armoured fighting vehicles from Novotoshkivke attacked Donetskyi supported by 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/29/kievskie-siloviki-obstrelyali-poselok-donetskij-v-lnr/|title=Киевские силовики обстреляли поселок Донецкий в ЛНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-07-08|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the evening pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 12 occasions, one Ukrainian soldier was wounded.<ref name=FB_6pm_06-29>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/399415423884413?_fb_noscript=1 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 29 червня 2018 року|trans-title= |date=2018-06-29 |accessdate=2018-06-29 |publisher=Press-centre of the JF HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 34, another Ukrainian serviceman was wounded. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, separatist forces fired small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers at Ukrainian positions near Verkhnyotoretske, Avdiivka, Marinka and Pisky. Sniper fire was reported at Nevelske. In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Pavlopil. Hnutove and Berdyansk were hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Ukrainian forces at Lebedinske, Shyrokyne, Vodiane, Pavlopil, and Novomihaylivka became the target of infantry weapons and rocket launchers. In the northern section of the demarcation line, pro-Russian tanks attacked Ukrainian redoubts at Novotoshkivke for the second consecutive day, while armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Maiske. Luhanske and Krymske were shelled with 82&nbsp;mm mortars, and Luhanske, Krymske, Svitlodarsk, Novhorodske and Novozvanivka were fired at from small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers.<ref name=MoD7am06-30>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/06/30/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-07-00-30-chervnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07:00 30 червня 2018 року |trans-title=|date=30 June 2018 |accessdate=30 June 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/war/10170266-jfo-ukraine-reports-2-wia-s-amid-34-enemy-attacks-in-donbas.html |publisher=UNIAN|title=JFO: Ukraine reports 2 WIA's amid 34 enemy attacks in Donbas {{!}} According to intelligence reports, three militants of the Russian occupation forces were killed and another two wounded.|date=2018-06-30 |accessdate=2018-06-30}}</ref><ref name="OOS-06-30" /> Pro-Russian officials told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on a number of occasions by evening. In the surroundings of Donetsk city, Ukrainian tanks from Nikolaevka opened fire on pro-Russian redoubts at Dokuchaievsk, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Bohdanivka and Novotroitske attacked pro-Russian positions at Petrovske and Yasne.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-iz-tanka-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ из танка обстреляли Докучаевск - СЦКК]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-petrovskoe-i-yasnoe-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Петровское и Ясное - СЦКК / AFU shelled Petrovskoye and Yasnoye – JCCC]</ref>

=== 30 June ===
According to the information provided by the press-centre of the JFO headquarters in the morning pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 34 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<ref name=MoD7am06-30/><!--2 WIA--> (including on 20 occasions in Donetsk region and on 14 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=OOS-06-30/>); the fire was returned on 18 occasions.<ref name=OOS-06-30/> By morning of 30 June three ceasefire violations were registered with no casualties on the Ukrainian side; the fire was returned twice.<ref name=OOS-06-30/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 29 June.<ref name=OOS-06-30>{{cite web|url=http://mediarnbo.org/2018/06/30/oos-svodnyie-dannyie-30-iyunya-2018/?lang=ru |title=ООС: сводные данные – 30 июня 2018 |trans-title=JFO&nbsp;– Summary information as of 30 June 2018|date=30 June 2018 |accessdate=30 June 2018 |publisher=NSDC |language=ru |website=mediarnbo.org|quote=Posted By: Galat 12:30 30/06/2018}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported four Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in four different locations employing 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers. armoured fighting vehicles and tanks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://donetsk24.su/news/ezhednevnaia-svodka-narushenii-rezhima-prekrashcheniia-ognia-za-period-s-3-00-29-iiunia-po-3-00-30-iiunia-stckk/|title=Ежедневная сводка нарушений режима прекращения огня за период с 3:00 29 июня по 3:00 30 июня - СЦКК|last=24|first=Донецк|website=Донецк 24|language=Russian|access-date=2018-07-08}}</ref> The same sources recorded 46 Ukrainian violations of the truce over the past week; Ukrainian forces fired 45 shells from 122&nbsp;mm self-propeleld artillery, 34 tank rounds, 119 shells from 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars and 321 shots from armoured fighting vehicles. Two pro-Russian soldiers were wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/29/vsu-za-nedelyu-poryadka-pyatidesyati-raz-narushili-rezhim-tishiny-v-dnr/|title=ВСУ за неделю порядка пятидесяти раз нарушили режим тишины в ДНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-07-08|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local authorities, Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire three times within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to engage pro-Russian positions at Donetskyi, Lohvynove and Sokolniki.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/06/30/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-tri-poselka-poter-net/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка — обстреляны три поселка, потерь нет|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-07-08|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that from 7:00&nbsp;am to 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian military had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 2 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pressjfo.news/posts/400294517129837 |title=Операція об'єднаних сил / Joint forces operation {{!}} Зведення станом на 18:00 30 червня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-06-30 |accessdate=2018-06-30 |publisher=Press-centre of the JFO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day total 26 ceasefire violations were registered, as a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded. In the region of Donetsk, Krasnohorivka, Avdiivka, Opytne, Novomykhailivka, Marinka and Pisky became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and antitank rocket launchers. Antitank rockets landed in Vesele. In the region of Mariupol, 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds landed in Hnutove, while infantry weapons and different types of grenade launchers were fired at Lebedinske, Vodiane, Pavlopil, Talakivka and Chermalyk. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Novotoshkivke was fired at from infantry weapons, grenade launchers, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian positions at Zaitseve and Yuzhne, supported by small arms and heavy machine gun fire.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/07/01/zvedennya-shhodo-obstanovki-v-rajoni-provedennya-operaczii-obednanih-sil-stanom-na-07-00-01-lipnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення щодо обстановки в районі проведення операції Об’єднаних сил станом на 07.00 01 липня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=1 July 2018 |accessdate=1 July 2018 |publisher=[[Ministry of Defence (Ukraine)|MoD]] |language=uk}}</ref> A number of ceasefire violations were reported by pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city by evening, when Zaitseve and 6/7 mining complex near Horlivka were attacked by Ukrainian forces. Pro-Russian positions at Zaitseve became the target of small arms, automatic grenade launchers and 82&nbsp;mm mortars, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles opened fire on 6/7 mining complex supported by small arms and automatic grenade launchers. BMP-1 armoured vehicles opened fire on pro-Russian redoubts at Verkhnyoshyrokivske.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-zajtsevo-i-gorlovku-iz-granatometov-i-bmp-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Зайцево и Горловку из гранатометов и БМП - СЦКК|last=|first=|date=30 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=1 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-zajtsevo-stskk-6/|title=Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Зайцево - СЦКК|last=|first=|date=30 June 2018|website=Официальный сайт ДНР|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=1 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-chetyre-raza-otkryvali-ogon-po-territorii-respubliki-stskk/|title=ВСУ четыре раза открывали огонь по территории Республики - СЦКК|last=|first=|date=1 July 2018|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=1 July 2018}}</ref>

